1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:01,400
We're going to ask for Mercan's hand tomorrow.

2
00:00:01,560 --> 00:00:02,840
What asking, son, have you lost your mind!?

3
00:00:03,080 --> 00:00:04,560
You're already married.

4
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:06,000
We've been through difficult times.

5
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:07,760
But now I want us to get better.

6
00:00:08,120 --> 00:00:09,200
Look, Haydar is in prison,

7
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:12,480
he got the punishment he deserved. Isn't that what we wanted?

8
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:14,600
After everything that happened…

9
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:16,360
Yes. Especially because of that.

10
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,840
That woman is going to ask for you from me, huh?

11
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:22,320
But I don't trust Müzeyyen.

12
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,120
Like I said...

13
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:26,480
That woman is a devil.

14
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:30,480
If I am bad, she is a thousand times worse than me.

15
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:33,440
Yes. Believe me.

16
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:36,200
They're going to ask for Mercan's hand, and you don't even tell me!

17
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:38,240
Brother, please!

18
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:39,280
What's going on here?

19
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,200
Please, don't cause any trouble today, please.

20
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:43,880
My brother is leaving anyway.

21
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:45,120
It'd be better if he left.

22
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,400
By the command of God and the word of the Prophet...

23
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,840
I ask for Mercan's hand for my son Ateş.

24
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:52,560
There we go.

25
00:00:58,320 --> 00:01:01,800
I will make you suffer what you made me suffer, Ateş Karahan.

26
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:04,640
All of it!

27
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:11,080
You've been on this journey with Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

28
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:14,400
Every twist, every heartbreak. Every moment.

29
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:17,240
And now we reach the end.

30
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,160
This isn't something to watch alone.

31
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:21,480
This is something we experience together.

32
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:27,040
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not be available on any memberships.

33
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:30,600
They will premiere on YouTube for all of us at the same time.

34
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,120
One moment.

35
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:35,000
One story. One ending.

36
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,560
So grab your comfy blanket and a huge bucket

37
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:40,560
of popcorn for one final twist.

38
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,640
Let's be there together.

39
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,160
It suits you.

40
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,560
I think so too.

41
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,800
It still feels like a dream.

42
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,840
I sometimes find it hard to believe.

43
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,920
When we were about to divorce, now we're in the middle of wedding preparations.

44
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:49,480
By the command of God and the word of the Prophet.

45
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,640
I'm still amazed.

46
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:53,960
The asking ceremony went smoothly too

47
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,480
I was already sure.

48
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:58,960
I got the girl, thank God.

49
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:04,520
Now we're going to where it all began…

50
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,040
Yes.

51
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:10,760
That's where my mind first got confused about you.

52
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:15,680
I noticed something stirring in my heart,

53
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,960
but I guess I couldn't quite place it.

54
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:22,640
When you acted all gruff and erratic like that.

55
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:23,840
One way, then another.

56
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:27,200
But you loved me with that gruffness.

57
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,960
You were smitten at first sight.

58
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:31,200
No way. Not at all.

59
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:34,640
I mean… At most, we could say I was intrigued at first sight.

60
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:35,840
Yeah, yeah.

61
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,760
It was obvious from your looks.

62
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,120
It was obvious from your looks, actually.

63
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:43,760
Constantly coming right up next to me, hovering around me…

64
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,000
It was obvious, so why didn't you understand?

65
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,120
Why did you make me work so hard?

66
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,120
I'm not hiding that I've been in love since the first moment.

67
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,480
It feels like just yesterday.

68
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,680
I love this house so much.

69
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:02,640
Maybe it's because our love first had a chance to breathe there…

70
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,040
And as soon as it got that chance, it blossomed.

71
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:11,120
Despite all the confusion, despite all the problems.

72
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,960
I guess that's destiny for you.

73
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,600
That house was really good for us.

74
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,160
It made us who we are…

75
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,600
We first started becoming 'us' there.

76
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:32,040
Uncle Durmuş and Aunt Güllü will be so surprised when we tell them about the wedding.

77
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,120
What happened?

78
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:54,840
Nothing… I just slowed down.

79
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,160
Do you remember the day we first came here?

80
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,120
How could I forget.

81
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:08,080
When I think about what we've been through…

82
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:12,280
I mean, where we started and where we are now.

83
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,840
From two people who couldn't stand each other,

84
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,080
we turned into two lovers who can't be apart.

85
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,520
We're not exactly normal, are we…

86
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,080
Wait, what are you doing?

87
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,880
I love you! I love you!

88
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,280
Get it through your head already!

89
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,120
-I don't love you! -Yes, you do!

90
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:13,280
-I don't love you, let go! -You do, admit it!

91
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,120
-I said I don't love you! -You do!

92
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,520
I love you so much!

93
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,040
So much… So much.

94
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:25,200
Who wants to be normal anyway.

95
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,960
I'm happy with us.

96
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,680
Though…

97
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,040
If I'd known you were this crazy,

98
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,760
I might have reconsidered.

99
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,160
Is that so, Mr. Ateş.

100
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Well, you didn't make it easy for me.

101
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,800
Nope, I did too little.

102
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:44,840
When it comes to making someone suffer, you get the gold medal.

103
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,560
I wouldn't underestimate yourself.

104
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,680
You really put me through the wringer…

105
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,680
Just setting out on the road brings peace.

106
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:29,400
You're distracting me. You're going to make me crash.

107
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,440
Oh, don't do that.

108
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,800
Look. Fasten your seatbelt.

109
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,360
Okay...

110
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:21,720
My daughter… How are you?

111
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,280
As if you care.

112
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,360
What kind of talk is that, Aslı.

113
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:33,320
Is there anyone in this world I care about more than you?

114
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:36,080
Is that why you're killing me? Because you care?

115
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,400
I saw everything yesterday!

116
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,760
You asked for that girl for Ateş.

117
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:44,480
I won't forgive you.

118
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:47,800
Aslı.

119
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:51,320
We have no choice but to accept Mercan.

120
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,240
See that now, my daughter.

121
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:02,320
Go on, drink.

122
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,200
Would you leave me alone?

123
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:21,560
Where did you two just pop out from…

124
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:24,000
I'm so glad, so glad to see you!

125
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,840
We wanted to see you.

126
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:28,440
Sit down, please. Sit down, my girl.

127
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,680
Ateş, you go sit next to your wife.

128
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:34,360
Alright, the kids know where to sit, I'm sure.

129
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:35,440
So?

130
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:38,720
How are you kids? You look really well.

131
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:40,880
We're fine, thank you.

132
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,320
You look well too.

133
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,280
Mashallah, you never age.

134
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,480
We're glad to see you too.

135
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:51,400
There's color in your face. You looked very pale last time we saw you.

136
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:55,120
It was so good of you to come.

137
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,520
You're staying, right?

138
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,960
-They'll stay, they'll stay. -Actually...

139
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,080
They'll stay, they'll stay.

140
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:04,240
Honestly, I feel overjoyed whenever I see you.

141
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,120
You've come right on time, huh.

142
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:08,960
Why?

143
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:12,160
We're moving out in two days.

144
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,200
You're moving?

145
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:20,080
What's the matter, Brother Durmuş, what's the reason?

146
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,320
We sold the house, son.

147
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:24,000
We're moving to the vineyard house.

148
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:28,520
Old age is hard, this house needs a lot of work, we can't manage anymore.

149
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:35,200
Yes. The vineyard house has two small rooms.

150
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,760
Less work too.

151
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:40,760
At this age, we need convenience…

152
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:44,360
What can we say. May it be for the best.

153
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:47,920
Yes, whatever is good for you.

154
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:52,600
-But this place holds a special place in our hearts… -Oh, dear!

155
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,280
Well, my girl...

156
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:57,680
We spent our youth here too.

157
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:01,080
My wife and I, we've been through so many days here, good and bad.

158
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:03,080
We took good care of our home.

159
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,960
And it sheltered us.

160
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:10,000
After all, once there's love in a house, only then does it become a home.

161
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:10,800
Exactly.

162
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:14,800
Otherwise, it's all just materials, stone, concrete.

163
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:17,280
Whether it's for the rich or the poor…

164
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:21,240
The trick is combining the material with love.

165
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,880
You're right, Uncle Durmuş.

166
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,200
May it be for the best, don't upset yourselves.

167
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,200
You're right, Uncle Durmuş.

168
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:36,480
Love is at the foundation of this house.

169
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,600
And what it makes me feel is…

170
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:41,440
Peace.

171
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:49,520
Maybe because it's the most loving house I've ever seen in my life,

172
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,320
this place is very different for me.

173
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,720
Everything I needed,

174
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:56,080
everything I missed, is here…

175
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:56,920
My dear.

176
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,440
We came one last time without knowing.

177
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,240
Mercan?

178
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:06,320
I got emotional all of a sudden.

179
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,840
My emotional wife.

180
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,120
Hey, you were happy the kids came!

181
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,640
Are we going to sit our guests hungry…

182
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:14,840
-Come on, let's prepare some things. -Of course I was happy.

183
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:17,520
-I'll get the food ready right away. -Go on then.

184
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:20,040
Let me help you too.

185
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,080
Malik?

186
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:45,480
What did you do?

187
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:48,360
I took care of all the paperwork, everything is ready.

188
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,000
I'm ready to hit the road.

189
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,440
Are the documents ready too?

190
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,720
All set, everything's taken care of.

191
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,240
God bless Mr. Cemal, he expedited things, so it's all done.

192
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:58,040
We got the tickets for tomorrow evening.

193
00:13:58,480 --> 00:13:59,320
Good, at least.

194
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,280
Just go and come back safely as soon as possible.

195
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:03,720
Your father will get better too, God willing…

196
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:06,680
He will get better, God willing. Don't worry.

197
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:10,080
Then we'll start the wedding preparations.

198
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,680
No more separations after this.

199
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:14,080
Everything will work out.

200
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,640
We'll do it all.

201
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,720
As long as there's health first.

202
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,160
The rest is easy.

203
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:23,760
You're so understanding…

204
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:27,000
I think about how lucky I am.

205
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:30,080
I must be a beloved servant of God, for Him to have brought you into my life.

206
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:32,720
There's no other way to explain this much luck.

207
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:35,320
Okay, stop, you'll give us the evil eye.

208
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,360
God forbid.

209
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,080
Malik…

210
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,360
I am very lucky too.

211
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:42,600
You know that, right…

212
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:43,880
My love…

213
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:45,720
We are each other's luck.

214
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:49,720
-I love you so much. -Me too.

215
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,000
Zahide.

216
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,920
Are you up for another rock concert?

217
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,880
Well, that state you were in was something.

218
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:30,880
I mean, considering you're usually so cold…

219
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,960
We all feel cold just looking at you.

220
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:38,720
It feels like these places are so dark and mysterious when you're not at the office.

221
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:43,520
Can you not go a single moment without teasing or joking?

222
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:49,560
It's not in my job description. You know you're not obligated, right…

223
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,120
I am obligated.

224
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:53,600
My day just doesn't go well if I don't do this.

225
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,280
I can't feel good otherwise.

226
00:15:57,200 --> 00:16:01,440
Think of it like not being able to wake up without coffee.

227
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:07,880
I need to raise the adrenaline in the environment. We need to feel all buzzy and excited.

228
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:09,560
I need to bring the energy.

229
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:12,160
Yes, I understand.

230
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,560
You're right, yes…

231
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:14,480
But…

232
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:17,200
We're the ones who are exposed to it, you know?

233
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,320
A person thinks, what's the point of this, normally.

234
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:24,840
One day we'll just drop dead from your excess adrenaline.

235
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,240
Nothing will happen, Zahide.

236
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:31,080
A little CPR, a kiss of life, good as new.

237
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,240
Everything will be fine.

238
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:36,960
Just a small one.

239
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:39,760
Right here…

240
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:41,520
Good morning.

241
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:43,960
Are we awake?

242
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:46,400
-Good morning. -Good morning.

243
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:47,640
We're awake.

244
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,120
Good morning.

245
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:55,320
-The asking ceremony went really well yesterday, didn't it. -Yes.

246
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,320
I was afraid something would go wrong,

247
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,760
but thank God, nothing happened.

248
00:16:58,880 --> 00:16:59,760
Oh, come on, Demet...

249
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:01,760
My sibling's happiest day.

250
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:05,520
No one would have dared to do anything while I was there.

251
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:09,480
Especially with me there. Never.

252
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:13,680
No one could have done a thing.

253
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,400
We're having a meeting, Mrs. Zahide.

254
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:23,720
Ateş won't be attending. Please inform the team.

255
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,000
Okay, Mr. Cemal.

256
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,040
Let me answer this phone.

257
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:38,040
Yes, my brother?

258
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,240
Hello, Cemal.

259
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:41,400
I need to ask you for something.

260
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:43,080
Anything you want.

261
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,520
Uncle Durmuş sold his house.

262
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,360
Find out who bought it for me.

263
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:51,360
I can find out but… why?

264
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:58,040
Maybe we can buy this house for Mercan.

265
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,080
She loves this place.

266
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,200
I'm thinking of doing something nice for her.

267
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:04,400
I understand.

268
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,480
Ateş Karahan is up to his usual classy moves for his wife…

269
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:08,800
Okay.

270
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:12,320
I'll find out who bought the house and get back to you.

271
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:13,760
Thank you.

272
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:23,360
Ateş called.

273
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:25,160
Uncle Durmuş...

274
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:28,160
They sold their house. Ateş wants to find the buyer

275
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,600
and buy the house for Mercan.

276
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,600
Love-related matters, I mean…

277
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:37,240
Romance, etc. Strange business.

278
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:00,720
Shh…

279
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:02,920
Don't be sad anymore.

280
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,840
I can't help it.

281
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,240
I realized I've grown too attached to this place.

282
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:17,280
The thought of a stranger living here…

283
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:21,120
Anyway… Never mind.

284
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:25,920
I won't mind.

285
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:33,880
Since we won't be able to come here again,

286
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:37,400
let's make our time here

287
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,040
valuable.

288
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:41,560
What does my beautiful wife want to do?

289
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:43,440
I don't know.

290
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:46,720
Nothing comes to mind at a moment like this.

291
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:50,360
Shall we walk in the garden?

292
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:52,320
Okay.

293
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:53,840
But dress warmly.

294
00:19:54,840 --> 00:19:56,240
I'm already dressed warmly.

295
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:57,600
You dress warmly.

296
00:19:58,960 --> 00:19:59,680
Actually…

297
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:02,320
-Let me take this off then. -No.

298
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:10,040
Wear it over yours. It'll be warmer, keep you cosy.

299
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,760
What happened? Why are you running away?

300
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,080
Nothing happened. I'm not running.

301
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,720
Then you're wearing this too.

302
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:35,400
No going out dressed lightly.

303
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,200
You'll get sick later, come on, put it on.

304
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,320
Turn around now.

305
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,160
Button up the front too.

306
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,200
Hold it with your hands.

307
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:53,600
Now we can go.

308
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:08,400
Report, what's the situation!

309
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:09,800
They arrived at the village house.

310
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,440
But I think she noticed me.

311
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:12,920
She slowed down.

312
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:15,800
I overtook Ateş and passed by so as not to arouse suspicion.

313
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:18,480
Good move. Stay at a distance.

314
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,720
Don't take your eyes off them.

315
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:23,200
Where they are, what they're doing, I need to know everything.

316
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,360
Inform the other men too. Let them be ready.

317
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:28,560
Okay.

318
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:29,680
By the way...

319
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:34,280
That village house they went to, it seems to have been sold recently.

320
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:36,600
Find out who bought it for me.

321
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,800
In fact, the moment you find out, offer double to buy it.

322
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:42,200
I need to buy that house before Ateş does.

323
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,200
Do whatever it takes, make sure he accepts.

324
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,720
Got it, I'll handle it and call you.

325
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,040
Mercan...

326
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,000
I won't let you have that house either…

327
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,760
This time you'll see who Nezir Keseroğlu is.

328
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,760
Uncle Durmuş was so right about what makes this house beautiful, wasn't he.

329
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,200
That's experience for you.

330
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:23,640
The wisdom that nothing else in life can give you,

331
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:25,200
only experience can.

332
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:27,840
He spoke from his life.

333
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,440
That's why what he said felt so real…

334
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:34,760
May love never be missing from our home, Ateş.

335
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,960
Even on our worst days,

336
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:41,600
even in our angriest moments, let's always feel it.

337
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:45,280
Hasn't it always been like that until now…

338
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,760
We've rehearsed this, Mercan.

339
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,360
Even on the hardest days,

340
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,600
I felt your heart.

341
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,200
If I managed to stay standing,

342
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:58,240
it was thanks to your love…

343
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:11,040
If your chat is over, time to work, kids…

344
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:13,600
Here, take these.

345
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:20,160
Tell us what to do, quickly.

346
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,720
Look, you see these...

347
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:27,520
I planted those trees with Güllü fifty years ago.

348
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:30,360
Look how they've become big trees.

349
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:34,400
You two will plant this one.

350
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:36,800
Since you say you love this place so much,

351
00:23:37,120 --> 00:23:38,960
leave a mark of yourselves.

352
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:43,640
Let it live on here in your name after you're gone…

353
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:46,360
As it grows, as it gets stronger,

354
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,440
wherever you are,

355
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,840
your love will grow stronger too.

356
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:53,480
Look, if you give even a drop of love

357
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:57,120
to the world...

358
00:23:57,920 --> 00:24:00,120
the world will not leave you unanswered…

359
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:02,560
Come on, back to work!

360
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:04,480
Go on, go on!

361
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:08,920
Isn't it beautiful? A tree that belongs to both of us will be here.

362
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:11,440
Yes, come on, time to work.

363
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,800
Dig a bit faster. Shove it in properly.

364
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,120
I am digging.

365
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:30,680
Stop talking and get the shovel.

366
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:40,360
Here.

367
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:53,800
Well, you're holding the shovel wrong… Is this your first time?

368
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:56,960
If you struggle like that for hours, you'll never finish.

369
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,800
The tree has already started growing on the spot.

370
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:00,600
So I'm holding it wrong?

371
00:25:00,720 --> 00:25:02,040
Yes…

372
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:04,680
Let me teach you.

373
00:25:06,040 --> 00:25:09,520
Hold it here, and push it in with your foot.

374
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:10,680
More powerful.

375
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:14,200
Look, I didn't know that.

376
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:17,560
Here, take this.

377
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,080
What are you doing?

378
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:24,160
Since I'm holding it wrong, show me how it's done properly.

379
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,600
Of course I will. Watch closely…

380
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:29,400
I'm watching.

381
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:33,680
Watch carefully. This is how it's done.

382
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:07,520
What happened, my wife?

383
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:09,560
Nothing.

384
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:15,440
Alright then. You've learned. Here, take it.

385
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:16,600
No, no, I haven't learned yet.

386
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,400
-You have, you have. -Dig a little more.

387
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:20,920
You've learned. You're smart.

388
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,080
No, I didn't quite understand.

389
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:24,080
I got a draft in my back.

390
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:26,240
I feel terrible, I can't move.

391
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:46,280
A draft, huh?

392
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:51,280
You will never interfere with your husband's work again.

393
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:54,800
I can't promise that.

394
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:58,320
Well, we'll figure that out over time…

395
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:08,480
What are you doing?

396
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,160
Someone might see, it's shameful.

397
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:12,480
So what, there's no one around.

398
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:14,000
You've really lost it!

399
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:17,320
Come on, take it.

400
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:31,960
Come on, faster.

401
00:27:32,520 --> 00:27:33,760
Work a little.

402
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:49,640
Help me take this bag off.

403
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:23,080
May our love take root and grow along with this sapling.

404
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:29,560
Maybe years later, our path will lead us here again, and we'll come see it.

405
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:31,160
Why not?

406
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,000
I already loved this house.

407
00:28:40,120 --> 00:28:41,560
Now I love it even more.

408
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:45,240
Now there's a part of us here too.

409
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:49,680
Yes.

410
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:55,720
Belonging to both of us.

411
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:01,920
Only us.

412
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,120
Mother.

413
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:34,920
Did you finish, my girl?

414
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:36,480
I chopped the onions.

415
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:40,000
I also took out the preserves. Look at this.

416
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:42,560
It smells lovely.

417
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:44,320
Oh, lovely.

418
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:47,200
Nothing beats summer tomatoes.

419
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,680
Yes, they're really good. What did you do, my girl...

420
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:52,040
Did you finish the rooms at the mansion?

421
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,040
No, a little bit is left.

422
00:29:54,120 --> 00:30:00,520
Leave this to me. You finish those so Mother Müzeyyen doesn't complain.

423
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:01,800
Okay, then.

424
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:03,280
Go on, dear.

425
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:23,800
Binnaz, hello.

426
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:26,760
Hello, Mrs. Nermin…

427
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:29,200
Are you alright?

428
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:34,040
I am not alright, Binnaz.

429
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:38,600
I saw Murat in my dream again.

430
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,800
I miss my son so much, so much.

431
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:52,120
So much…

432
00:30:57,360 --> 00:30:59,400
May God have mercy on him.

433
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:01,800
He wanted a prayer from us.

434
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:04,920
That's why I came.

435
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:07,440
Let's give out some food today.

436
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:09,600
Let the kids distribute it.

437
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,520
Of course, Mrs. Nermin.

438
00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:14,560
I'll do it. For the blessings.

439
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:21,080
My child is gone, turned to soil.

440
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:29,200
I don't want to grieve.

441
00:31:31,800 --> 00:31:35,640
I try not to show it, but it doesn't work, Binnaz. I can't.

442
00:31:41,040 --> 00:31:42,400
They caused my son's death.

443
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,800
They caused it.

444
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:53,720
Anyway…

445
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,280
You'll handle it, Binnaz.

446
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:58,120
Don't worry. I'll start right away.

447
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,920
Take care of yourself.

448
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,120
Oh, Binnaz, Binnaz.

449
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:25,680
Again, you couldn't say that he's not her son.

450
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:29,200
What would change if I did?

451
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:32,160
The woman thinks Murat is her son.

452
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:34,680
No...

453
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:39,360
I cannot carry this burden any longer.

454
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:43,520
I won't be able to answer for this on the other side.

455
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:46,560
God, forgive me.

456
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:58,440
Do you remember…

457
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:02,680
Once you wanted to replant a flower, but it didn't take.

458
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:06,640
I don't remember.

459
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:09,760
You barely held back from crying.

460
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:18,000
I do like working with soil anyway.

461
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:19,840
Guess what?

462
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:22,520
Let's fill our garden with trees.

463
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:24,480
Lots of fruit trees.

464
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,000
And all kinds!

465
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,200
Our children can pick fruit from the branches.

466
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:34,200
Let's plant all kinds.

467
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:38,120
Plum, pomegranate, cherry, peach…

468
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:40,320
What happened?

469
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:42,880
Nothing.

470
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:47,280
Something happened. You seemed to flinch…

471
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:49,600
The air got cold too, you'll catch a chill. Shall we go in?

472
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:51,600
No, I'm not cold.

473
00:33:52,040 --> 00:33:53,280
Don't change the subject.

474
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,320
Are you telling me that when I said 'peach'...

475
00:33:58,520 --> 00:33:59,480
Ateş!

476
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,240
I don't believe it. Really…

477
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:03,360
Mercan!

478
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:06,120
I've learned another wonderful thing about you.

479
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:08,600
You get all weird when someone says 'peach'.

480
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:10,480
Are you going to say it again, huh!?

481
00:34:11,080 --> 00:34:14,560
Honestly, Ateş. I just said 'peach'.

482
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:15,440
Mercan!

483
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:16,680
We'll have a fight, you know.

484
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,720
I'm hurt, Ateş.

485
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:22,280
Telling me off as if I'd said something bad.

486
00:34:22,720 --> 00:34:23,800
I'm upset.

487
00:34:24,520 --> 00:34:26,160
Just for saying 'peach'…

488
00:34:26,200 --> 00:34:27,120
Mercan!

489
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:30,000
-Come here! -Peach!

490
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:34,120
Peach!

491
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,280
Peach!

492
00:34:50,960 --> 00:34:52,480
Peach! Peach!

493
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,320
Are you going to say it again?

494
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:13,400
I don't know.

495
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,480
Say it one more time, if you want.

496
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:18,600
Okay, I won't say it again.

497
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:23,080
Everything I discover about you, I like so much…

498
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:28,320
Even this little detail is so huge…

499
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:32,080
Discovering you… Getting to know you…

500
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:34,200
It's like finding myself…

501
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:38,880
But no matter what…

502
00:35:39,840 --> 00:35:40,960
Peach!

503
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:45,120
Peach!

504
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:09,560
Çiçek!

505
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:12,160
Malik…

506
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:18,240
You're leaving, aren't you? You won't be gone too long?

507
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:21,920
I mean, worst case, let's say work takes longer, you'll come and go.

508
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:24,760
How long can I be apart from you anyway?

509
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:30,480
I'll see my father, hopefully heal him, and come back right away.

510
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:32,000
I hope so.

511
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:35,240
Besides, you don't need to be scared anymore.

512
00:36:37,520 --> 00:36:38,720
Look what I have for you.

513
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,480
-What is it? -Open it and see.

514
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:48,440
Can you hold this?

515
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:51,280
Where did this come from?

516
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:54,760
This…

517
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:57,320
Until I come back,

518
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:00,440
all the bad dreams, all the bad thoughts you have,

519
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:02,200
will be trapped inside this.

520
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:04,840
That way, you'll only think of good things.

521
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:10,560
Like… how much I love you.

522
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:17,040
How much I'll miss you.

523
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,520
Things like that, you know.

524
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:28,880
I'll hang this by my bedside.

525
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,240
I'll only think of good things.

526
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:32,920
Deal.

527
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:34,680
Deal.

528
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:39,040
I love you so much.

529
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:41,200
Me too…

530
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:48,280
This is so beautiful.

531
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:09,440
Yes…

532
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:11,960
I found out who they sold the house to.

533
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:13,400
I also made the offer.

534
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,640
Okay, stay on top of it.

535
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,480
Handle it securely.

536
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:25,080
That place will be mine.

537
00:38:33,840 --> 00:38:35,720
All means are acceptable, remember that.

538
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,720
What kind of man are you!?

539
00:38:50,920 --> 00:38:52,320
Are you even a man?

540
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:56,600
You immediately went after the house, sneaking around.

541
00:38:56,720 --> 00:38:57,760
That's just like you.

542
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:00,560
What's the problem?

543
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:03,680
Did Ateş authorize you?

544
00:39:03,720 --> 00:39:07,160
Nezir, watch your mouth, if I fix it for you, I'll put it back wrong and ruin your face.

545
00:39:07,200 --> 00:39:08,440
-Cemal! -Decided to be a man now, have you?

546
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:11,840
Cemal, what are you doing? Go on.

547
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:19,360
I liked the house, I made an offer.

548
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:22,240
Do we need your permission to make an investment now!

549
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:24,560
Investment? You call this an investment?

550
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:27,040
You are so sick, man!

551
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,280
You're no different from Aslı.

552
00:39:35,760 --> 00:39:38,200
Your only job is to disturb the peace.

553
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:42,520
Leave them alone already.

554
00:39:43,080 --> 00:39:44,120
Last warning.

555
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:46,280
Things will get very ugly otherwise.

556
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:51,080
Look at the little one!

557
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:52,360
You listen to me good, man!

558
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:53,400
-Take your hand off me, man! -Bro!

559
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:55,360
Cemal, what are you doing!

560
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:03,280
Demet, are you okay?

561
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:05,360
Is anything wrong?

562
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:11,800
I'm sorry.

563
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,080
Demet, are you okay?

564
00:40:33,160 --> 00:40:34,080
It's nothing…

565
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:35,640
How can it be nothing?

566
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:38,720
Come on, let me take you to a doctor. Maybe it's broken.

567
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:40,720
It's fine, Cemal.

568
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:44,480
Don't interfere. It's not necessary.

569
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:49,440
Demet, look, your brother has lost his balance now.

570
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:52,080
Look, he's starting to hurt everyone.

571
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:55,120
You're seeing it with your own eyes.

572
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,200
He wouldn't hurt anyone on purpose.

573
00:40:59,680 --> 00:41:01,840
His love for Mercan has made him a bit aggressive, that's all…

574
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:05,080
That's why he makes mistakes like this.

575
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:06,920
He does make mistakes, that's true…

576
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:09,200
But it's not true that he's in love.

577
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:13,280
Your brother is sick. He can't think straight anymore.

578
00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:15,920
It's no different from what Aslı did.

579
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:20,400
Look, love isn't like that.

580
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:23,000
Love doesn't make a person bad.

581
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:27,040
Bad people just use love as an excuse for their badness. Like Nezir does.

582
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:30,360
I'm sorry but…

583
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:33,000
Your brother is just as bad as Aslı…

584
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:07,600
Here, let me fold it.

585
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:20,040
Being your husband feels amazing.

586
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:23,800
You never let me do anything.

587
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:26,920
Well…

588
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:31,680
What is it like being my wife…

589
00:42:38,120 --> 00:42:40,320
You talk, I'll go help set the table.

590
00:42:44,520 --> 00:42:45,080
Hello?

591
00:42:45,640 --> 00:42:47,200
Bad news, bro.

592
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:49,680
Nezir… He did it again.

593
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:51,760
He made an offer on the house.

594
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:55,640
He always has to cause trouble…

595
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,200
As if he has a checklist.

596
00:42:57,560 --> 00:42:59,840
Ticking things off!

597
00:43:00,280 --> 00:43:02,440
He's looking for every opportunity to get in my way.

598
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:06,320
I try to be a gentleman and step aside, but no.

599
00:43:06,880 --> 00:43:07,920
What ambition this guy has…

600
00:43:08,880 --> 00:43:11,600
I'm giving you full authority. Do whatever it takes…

601
00:43:13,560 --> 00:43:14,520
Handle this.

602
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:16,720
Don't you worry.

603
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:18,880
I'll do more than necessary.

604
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:20,760
Talk to you soon.

605
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:23,840
I forgot my phone.

606
00:43:27,680 --> 00:43:28,560
Is there a problem?

607
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:31,000
Something about work.

608
00:43:33,880 --> 00:43:36,680
Should I pretend to believe you? Or should I keep asking?

609
00:43:40,360 --> 00:43:41,480
Pretend.

610
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:46,480
Okay. Come on.

611
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:47,840
Food's ready, shall we go in…

612
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:05,840
You've been on this journey with Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

613
00:44:06,160 --> 00:44:09,160
Every twist, every heartbreak. Every moment.

614
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:12,000
And now we reach the end.

615
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:13,920
This isn't something to watch alone.

616
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:16,240
This is something we experience together.

617
00:44:16,240 --> 00:44:21,800
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not be available on any memberships.

618
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:25,360
They will premiere on YouTube for all of us at the same time.

619
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:26,880
One moment.

620
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:29,760
One story. One ending.

621
00:44:29,760 --> 00:44:32,320
So grab your comfy blanket and a huge bucket

622
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:35,320
of popcorn for one final twist.

623
00:44:35,440 --> 00:44:37,400
Let's be there together.

624
00:44:45,360 --> 00:44:47,320
Oh, how lovely…

625
00:44:48,600 --> 00:44:50,200
Exactly like in the movies.

626
00:44:51,680 --> 00:44:54,160
When destiny decides to write people for each other,

627
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:59,240
wherever they are, they will find their way to one another.

628
00:45:03,640 --> 00:45:07,280
What you struggle to attain is what becomes precious to you.

629
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:17,880
Güllü, get up, come on, I'm getting sleepy too.

630
00:45:17,920 --> 00:45:18,560
Come on, let's go to bed.

631
00:45:18,680 --> 00:45:20,720
Come on, then. May God give you rest.

632
00:45:21,600 --> 00:45:23,640
-Good night. -Good night.

633
00:45:23,760 --> 00:45:25,360
Good night, kids.

634
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:36,080
Well done, it was delicious.

635
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:38,240
Honestly, it was the best stuffed eggplant I've ever had.

636
00:45:39,760 --> 00:45:43,600
Well, your wife's hand touched it, so it must have tasted better to you.

637
00:45:47,680 --> 00:45:49,800
Yes… I made the filling.

638
00:45:50,600 --> 00:45:52,160
Why don't you believe me?

639
00:45:53,880 --> 00:45:57,360
By 'I made it', you probably just stirred it once or twice while it was cooking.

640
00:45:57,760 --> 00:45:59,480
No, I prepared it.

641
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:04,360
-I won't cook anymore then. -Okay, okay, come here.

642
00:46:06,440 --> 00:46:07,240
Don't be upset.

643
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:09,600
I will.

644
00:46:10,280 --> 00:46:11,880
I feel like sulking.

645
00:46:12,400 --> 00:46:15,560
I made a silly mistake. Forgive me.

646
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:18,240
Well done, my wife.

647
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:22,240
It was the best stuffed eggplant I've ever eaten.

648
00:46:22,680 --> 00:46:24,720
It was as if the queen of stuffed eggplants had made it.

649
00:46:25,560 --> 00:46:27,240
See, he's still making fun.

650
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:31,360
Nothing I say seems to work, I guess.

651
00:46:32,200 --> 00:46:34,480
There's roadwork on the way back.

652
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:36,200
You can't go back this way.

653
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:37,280
Is that so?

654
00:46:37,840 --> 00:46:38,560
Exactly.

655
00:46:40,520 --> 00:46:41,360
You know what…

656
00:46:43,240 --> 00:46:45,920
There are three things I don't understand about you.

657
00:46:46,760 --> 00:46:48,880
Oh? Only three?

658
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:52,760
Personally, I'm a bit disappointed.

659
00:46:53,760 --> 00:46:56,280
What are they, let's hear them.

660
00:46:57,160 --> 00:46:59,080
How can you get upset so easily?

661
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:05,600
Because I have a husband who constantly keeps me in a mood to sulk.

662
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:06,720
Give me the next one.

663
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:08,920
Why do you argue with everything I say?

664
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:14,560
It only seems like arguing because I don't agree with everything you say.

665
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:17,800
Anyway… So? Send the next one.

666
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:23,720
While doing all this,

667
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:26,680
how can you be so sweet and beautiful?

668
00:47:29,520 --> 00:47:30,760
It's because I love you so much.

669
00:47:32,680 --> 00:47:34,120
It's because you are so loved.

670
00:47:39,040 --> 00:47:41,080
Let me make you some tea.

671
00:47:46,680 --> 00:47:49,160
Yes, you make me tea.

672
00:49:03,560 --> 00:49:04,760
What are you doing here?

673
00:49:05,840 --> 00:49:08,960
I got bored of lying down, if you don't mind!

674
00:49:10,440 --> 00:49:12,040
What are you doing in this room?

675
00:49:12,880 --> 00:49:15,680
I just came in, I'm not doing anything!

676
00:49:16,480 --> 00:49:18,160
You never learn!

677
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:21,600
Whatever I do, I do for your own good…

678
00:49:22,280 --> 00:49:24,160
Then our understanding of 'good' is very different.

679
00:49:27,440 --> 00:49:29,160
Besides, I don't believe you anymore.

680
00:49:30,040 --> 00:49:31,840
I lost Ateş because of you.

681
00:49:35,320 --> 00:49:37,600
And now you're trying to knock me out with medication.

682
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:42,240
Is that your idea of good!

683
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:46,000
What happened?

684
00:49:47,720 --> 00:49:48,920
Do you think I didn't understand?

685
00:49:49,720 --> 00:49:51,360
Do you think I'm stupid?

686
00:49:54,800 --> 00:49:56,480
You left me no choice…

687
00:49:58,840 --> 00:50:01,240
Ateş doesn't want you at the mansion, my daughter.

688
00:50:04,120 --> 00:50:07,320
So I've been trying to calm you down, keep you out of sight.

689
00:50:11,160 --> 00:50:12,320
But since it's like this…

690
00:50:14,360 --> 00:50:15,880
you need to leave the mansion now.

691
00:50:32,120 --> 00:50:33,160
Come…

692
00:50:35,120 --> 00:50:36,320
I have a surprise for you.

693
00:50:38,560 --> 00:50:39,520
What surprise…

694
00:50:40,360 --> 00:50:41,200
Wait here.

695
00:50:55,800 --> 00:50:57,840
Uncle Durmuş had me clear out the shed today.

696
00:50:58,440 --> 00:50:59,240
Look what I found.

697
00:51:00,440 --> 00:51:01,360
A wish balloon…

698
00:51:15,480 --> 00:51:17,000
Come on… Have you made your wish?

699
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:26,760
No, wait a minute. I need to think.

700
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:30,720
Okay, okay.

701
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:32,480
No need to think.

702
00:52:19,400 --> 00:52:20,160
What did you wish for?

703
00:52:21,240 --> 00:52:22,040
You can't tell.

704
00:52:23,360 --> 00:52:27,200
Oh, come on… you have to tell me. I'll be curious.

705
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:29,240
No.

706
00:52:29,840 --> 00:52:31,680
If you want, you tell me yours.

707
00:52:32,600 --> 00:52:35,080
You have to say it for it to come true.

708
00:52:35,680 --> 00:52:37,240
You're very sweet, but I'm not convinced…

709
00:52:38,320 --> 00:52:40,000
If you want, you can say yours.

710
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:42,440
Okay.

711
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:44,240
Maybe I'll say mine after you.

712
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:47,680
Okay.

713
00:52:49,320 --> 00:52:50,800
I made two wishes.

714
00:52:52,200 --> 00:52:52,920
The first one…

715
00:52:54,840 --> 00:52:56,720
To always be with you and to be happy.

716
00:52:58,200 --> 00:52:59,200
And the second one…

717
00:52:59,760 --> 00:53:01,520
Maybe it'll sound silly to you but…

718
00:53:02,600 --> 00:53:03,520
I wished for this house.

719
00:53:04,280 --> 00:53:06,880
For a miracle to happen so we don't have to leave this house.

720
00:53:10,040 --> 00:53:12,440
I've told you mine. Your turn…

721
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:15,280
My wish is you.

722
00:53:18,160 --> 00:53:19,520
The rest is just details, Mrs. Mercan.

723
00:53:21,480 --> 00:53:23,920
I'm already by your side. Come on…

724
00:53:24,600 --> 00:53:26,880
You said if I said mine, you'd say yours…

725
00:53:27,560 --> 00:53:29,840
I said 'maybe' I would.

726
00:53:30,440 --> 00:53:31,040
Meaning?

727
00:53:31,800 --> 00:53:33,400
You're not going to tell me?

728
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:37,600
I'm sure, in the end…

729
00:53:41,600 --> 00:53:43,320
you'll find a way to make me tell you.

730
00:54:06,200 --> 00:54:07,600
My dear brother…

731
00:54:12,680 --> 00:54:17,440
It's cold in Egypt now. I don't know what winters are like there, but…

732
00:54:17,440 --> 00:54:21,400
You packed warm things, right? Sweaters, scarves?

733
00:54:22,280 --> 00:54:23,840
I did, Mother Binnaz.

734
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:25,720
Malik, take these too.

735
00:54:25,960 --> 00:54:28,400
I put in all healing herbs.

736
00:54:32,760 --> 00:54:36,040
If you feel bad, drink some right away.

737
00:54:37,520 --> 00:54:39,280
Okay. Thanks, Çiçek…

738
00:54:40,480 --> 00:54:41,400
You're welcome.

739
00:54:51,200 --> 00:54:52,000
Brother.

740
00:54:53,080 --> 00:54:54,240
There's a saying.

741
00:54:54,880 --> 00:54:58,280
A mountain cannot meet a mountain, but a person can meet a person.

742
00:54:59,520 --> 00:55:01,400
If something happens to you there…

743
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:04,000
if you need me,

744
00:55:04,040 --> 00:55:06,000
just say 'hello'.

745
00:55:06,480 --> 00:55:08,040
I'll jump on a plane and come.

746
00:55:18,440 --> 00:55:20,720
Though, I wonder if my phone works abroad…

747
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:24,800
You might call and not reach me.

748
00:55:26,360 --> 00:55:28,800
I'll sort that out and let you know.

749
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:32,080
Okay.

750
00:55:33,080 --> 00:55:34,400
Thanks, brother-in-law.

751
00:55:38,880 --> 00:55:40,360
Thank you all, you are all so kind.

752
00:55:41,400 --> 00:55:42,720
God bless you.

753
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:47,560
I will go and come back quickly.

754
00:55:50,680 --> 00:55:51,880
To reunite with my family.

755
00:55:55,240 --> 00:55:57,680
Your family will be waiting for you.

756
00:56:06,920 --> 00:56:07,400
Mother…

757
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:13,160
-Say something?! -What should I say, my son?

758
00:56:19,400 --> 00:56:24,080
Please convey our get-well wishes to your wife.

759
00:56:25,120 --> 00:56:25,680
Thank you.

760
00:56:26,520 --> 00:56:28,640
May he recover quickly, God willing.

761
00:56:30,240 --> 00:56:31,560
-Amen. -Amen.

762
00:56:47,200 --> 00:56:48,560
Excuse us.

763
00:56:49,040 --> 00:56:52,240
Have a safe journey. May God heal your father.

764
00:56:53,360 --> 00:56:55,000
What are you going to do with these empty things?

765
00:57:03,360 --> 00:57:04,520
I'll tell you what I found, mom.

766
00:57:06,160 --> 00:57:06,920
I found a family.

767
00:57:08,200 --> 00:57:09,800
I found tenderness, I found warmth.

768
00:57:10,800 --> 00:57:12,000
Have you ever asked yourself?

769
00:57:12,880 --> 00:57:13,800
Did your dad call me?

770
00:57:15,640 --> 00:57:17,640
How is my son?

771
00:57:18,880 --> 00:57:22,120
Comfortable? Happy? No.

772
00:57:23,560 --> 00:57:27,400
That's why you don't ask me again

773
00:57:29,560 --> 00:57:31,960
what you're going to do with these things, because these contain a family.

774
00:57:33,480 --> 00:57:34,680
Okay? Let's go.

775
00:57:36,720 --> 00:57:39,440
Then… Goodbye.

776
00:57:42,200 --> 00:57:42,800
Come on, mom.

777
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:56,960
-He must have said something good. -Of course.

778
00:58:00,440 --> 00:58:00,960
Of course.

779
00:58:03,160 --> 00:58:06,200
-May God reunite you. -Amen.

780
00:58:07,680 --> 00:58:09,720
Malik seemed a bit tense when he was leaving.

781
00:58:44,200 --> 00:58:45,320
What a night, though.

782
00:58:46,840 --> 00:58:48,880
Ateş, that's not fair though.

783
00:58:50,280 --> 00:58:51,160
Am I lying, dear?

784
00:58:54,160 --> 00:58:57,360
I couldn't sleep properly because of my racing heart.

785
00:59:00,680 --> 00:59:03,000
Aunt Güllü gave us a single pillow again.

786
00:59:08,480 --> 00:59:09,360
Is that so bad?

787
00:59:10,480 --> 00:59:11,560
It doesn't separate lovers.

788
00:59:28,240 --> 00:59:29,760
How much longer are you going to stare like that?

789
00:59:33,640 --> 00:59:34,760
I could stare forever.

790
00:59:37,120 --> 00:59:37,880
Won't you get tired?

791
00:59:40,840 --> 00:59:41,440
No.

792
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:47,800
You know, you and I…

793
00:59:48,760 --> 00:59:50,320
we didn't just cross mountains or deserts,

794
00:59:50,880 --> 00:59:53,120
we've literally crossed worlds, do you realize?

795
00:59:53,920 --> 00:59:55,880
I'm still amazed at the journey we've taken.

796
00:59:57,160 --> 00:59:59,680
It's not that much, actually.

797
01:00:00,360 --> 01:00:01,960
We just achieved the impossible…

798
01:00:03,320 --> 01:00:06,920
Yes, softening your heart really was impossible…

799
01:00:08,280 --> 01:00:10,600
If we're making a list of impossible things,

800
01:00:10,960 --> 01:00:13,280
breaking your stubbornness would top it, though.

801
01:00:13,760 --> 01:00:14,560
My stubbornness!

802
01:00:15,400 --> 01:00:17,840
You didn't even tell me your wish!

803
01:00:18,600 --> 01:00:20,840
You said after coffee, and I made you nice coffee.

804
01:00:21,160 --> 01:00:22,280
You still didn't tell me.

805
01:00:22,800 --> 01:00:26,000
You said after dessert, you finished the dessert. Still nothing.

806
01:00:33,160 --> 01:00:36,560
I wished for our children to grow up in the shade of the tree we planted today.

807
01:02:20,800 --> 01:02:21,560
Ateş?

808
01:02:49,920 --> 01:02:51,040
What's the status, Cemal?

809
01:02:51,960 --> 01:02:54,720
Ateş, the man won't budge.

810
01:02:55,960 --> 01:02:58,320
He seems likely to accept Nezir's offer.

811
01:02:58,720 --> 01:03:01,240
Nezir has opened his purse strings out of jealousy.

812
01:03:02,120 --> 01:03:02,960
Crazy guy.

813
01:03:04,440 --> 01:03:07,360
Send me the info for that man. Let me talk to him.

814
01:03:08,520 --> 01:03:10,400
Sending it right away.

815
01:03:11,160 --> 01:03:11,680
Wait.

816
01:03:12,600 --> 01:03:13,240
Okay.

817
01:03:33,240 --> 01:03:35,000
Ateş left the house, what should I do?

818
01:03:37,120 --> 01:03:37,920
Is Mercan at home?

819
01:03:38,840 --> 01:03:39,400
Yes.

820
01:03:39,880 --> 01:03:41,280
The old man and woman are also home.

821
01:03:42,240 --> 01:03:43,240
You stay there.

822
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:45,760
Let me know when Mercan is alone.

823
01:03:46,760 --> 01:03:47,400
Okay.

824
01:04:01,680 --> 01:04:04,280
Good morning…

825
01:04:04,680 --> 01:04:06,000
Good morning, my beautiful girl.

826
01:04:06,440 --> 01:04:07,720
Um…

827
01:04:08,360 --> 01:04:11,120
Where is Ateş? Is he in the garden?

828
01:04:12,600 --> 01:04:14,000
No, he's not in the garden.

829
01:04:14,120 --> 01:04:16,920
He left early, but he didn't say anything to us.

830
01:04:18,280 --> 01:04:19,080
Oh no.

831
01:04:34,080 --> 01:04:35,000
He's not answering…

832
01:04:35,880 --> 01:04:37,000
Where is that man?

833
01:04:37,680 --> 01:04:38,920
Don't get worried right away, my girl.

834
01:04:39,200 --> 01:04:40,520
He must have some business.

835
01:04:40,800 --> 01:04:42,160
He'll be back soon…

836
01:04:43,920 --> 01:04:46,200
He didn't even leave me a note…

837
01:04:47,480 --> 01:04:48,880
When he gets back, I'll ask him…

838
01:04:51,040 --> 01:04:52,480
Let me go downstairs and check.

839
01:04:52,640 --> 01:04:54,160
-Okay. -Okay.

840
01:04:55,880 --> 01:04:57,320
She got worried right away.

841
01:05:05,520 --> 01:05:07,040
When is Malik coming back?

842
01:05:07,800 --> 01:05:09,560
He went out, he'll be back soon.

843
01:05:38,040 --> 01:05:38,600
Hello?

844
01:05:41,840 --> 01:05:43,280
I'll stay here a little longer.

845
01:05:54,760 --> 01:05:55,880
Will you excuse me?

846
01:05:56,920 --> 01:05:58,440
Of course, of course. Go ahead.

847
01:06:05,560 --> 01:06:08,120
I wonder what that Pharaoh-like woman is up to now?

848
01:06:21,600 --> 01:06:22,480
He wants Çiçek.

849
01:06:24,280 --> 01:06:25,080
He doesn't want anyone else.

850
01:06:30,200 --> 01:06:30,880
Don't worry.

851
01:06:33,240 --> 01:06:34,120
I'll bring her with me.

852
01:06:35,640 --> 01:06:37,120
She's definitely up to something.

853
01:06:41,200 --> 01:06:44,080
Wait, let me get this recording translated so we can see what you're after…

854
01:06:58,680 --> 01:07:00,720
-Where is this man? -He'll be here.

855
01:07:01,120 --> 01:07:03,120
We discussed everything, we arranged it.

856
01:07:03,640 --> 01:07:05,680
We offered three times the amount the man quoted.

857
01:07:06,880 --> 01:07:08,600
He'd have to be an idiot to back out now.

858
01:07:09,400 --> 01:07:13,240
Whatever it costs, you'll pay it.

859
01:07:14,160 --> 01:07:16,240
I will never, ever let Ateş get that house.

860
01:07:17,120 --> 01:07:18,640
-Understood? -Got it.

861
01:07:20,560 --> 01:07:21,440
Go now!

862
01:07:22,480 --> 01:07:23,280
Where have you been?

863
01:07:31,160 --> 01:07:32,720
Okay, I understand.

864
01:07:33,080 --> 01:07:35,560
You understand me too. We've been talking for hours.

865
01:07:36,240 --> 01:07:39,440
But I suggest you reconsider our offer.

866
01:07:40,520 --> 01:07:44,040
Yes, money is important, but what's more important is gaining good people.

867
01:07:47,160 --> 01:07:48,960
Okay, we'll talk again.

868
01:08:07,480 --> 01:08:08,600
Demet isn't here yet…

869
01:08:14,000 --> 01:08:15,720
Demet is a sweet girl.

870
01:08:20,720 --> 01:08:21,920
And cheerful and all.

871
01:08:23,920 --> 01:08:24,440
So?

872
01:08:25,360 --> 01:08:26,520
What are you trying to say?

873
01:08:29,320 --> 01:08:31,880
Don't give me that look right away. I'm telling you for your own good.

874
01:08:32,400 --> 01:08:33,680
If you found someone, don't let her slip away.

875
01:08:37,600 --> 01:08:41,520
Besides, I think you two look great together.

876
01:08:43,560 --> 01:08:46,840
Yaşar, maybe you shouldn't get into this subject?

877
01:08:47,600 --> 01:08:50,440
If I don't get into it, you'll be sitting here

878
01:08:50,480 --> 01:08:52,680
staring at empty tables.

879
01:08:54,160 --> 01:08:55,600
I understand you…

880
01:08:56,440 --> 01:08:59,320
You're a decent guy. You can't express your feelings.

881
01:09:06,480 --> 01:09:08,560
Take some advice from your big brother…

882
01:09:09,200 --> 01:09:12,360
Once you find love, hold onto it with all your might, don't let go.

883
01:09:19,120 --> 01:09:20,560
If you love her, say it.

884
01:09:20,760 --> 01:09:23,040
Don't keep your love bottled up inside.

885
01:09:25,480 --> 01:09:26,120
Am I wrong?

886
01:09:31,480 --> 01:09:32,680
I saw you smile.

887
01:09:33,200 --> 01:09:34,520
You're not indifferent to her either.

888
01:09:43,200 --> 01:09:43,760
Umm...

889
01:09:48,560 --> 01:09:49,040
Good morning…

890
01:09:50,840 --> 01:09:51,240
Good morning…

891
01:09:54,200 --> 01:09:54,640
Good morning…

892
01:10:27,240 --> 01:10:28,280
Where is this man?

893
01:10:33,360 --> 01:10:33,920
Mercan.

894
01:10:37,360 --> 01:10:38,480
Where have you been?

895
01:10:39,640 --> 01:10:42,400
I went shopping. Got some simit…

896
01:10:43,480 --> 01:10:44,600
Where is Uncle Durmuş?

897
01:10:44,880 --> 01:10:45,880
They're in their room.

898
01:10:46,400 --> 01:10:48,000
Couldn't you have let me know?

899
01:10:48,440 --> 01:10:50,120
I was worried, I called but you didn't answer.

900
01:10:51,520 --> 01:10:54,760
You could have left a note, sent a message.

901
01:10:57,640 --> 01:10:58,240
Anyway…

902
01:10:58,920 --> 01:11:01,600
Honestly, if it weren't for the simit, I wouldn't forgive you, just so you know…

903
01:11:13,440 --> 01:11:15,160
-What is this? -Open it.

904
01:11:33,960 --> 01:11:34,520
Ateş?

905
01:11:40,320 --> 01:11:41,440
This house is yours now.

906
01:12:04,240 --> 01:12:04,720
But…

907
01:12:05,840 --> 01:12:06,520
But how?

908
01:12:38,760 --> 01:12:39,480
Hello.

909
01:12:40,680 --> 01:12:41,320
Hello.

910
01:12:42,080 --> 01:12:43,160
This is a secluded place.

911
01:12:43,760 --> 01:12:45,480
Not many people pass by, don't waste your time waiting…

912
01:12:46,360 --> 01:12:47,400
What are you doing here?

913
01:12:49,000 --> 01:12:50,680
I was going to ask you the same thing but…

914
01:12:52,680 --> 01:12:55,160
I don't waste time with questions I already know the answer to.

915
01:12:57,440 --> 01:12:58,680
I suggest you don't either.

916
01:13:00,040 --> 01:13:01,920
I think you should just leave, slowly.

917
01:13:03,040 --> 01:13:04,800
The person you're waiting for isn't coming.

918
01:13:06,080 --> 01:13:10,200
He can't sell a house he already sold, after all…

919
01:13:12,320 --> 01:13:13,200
What are you talking about!

920
01:13:14,760 --> 01:13:16,640
I bought the house, Nezir.

921
01:13:19,800 --> 01:13:20,640
What is he saying!

922
01:13:23,880 --> 01:13:26,680
Your mind might not grasp it, but there are things more valuable than money.

923
01:13:27,720 --> 01:13:29,960
Like humanity, like love.

924
01:13:30,960 --> 01:13:32,440
I was honest with the man.

925
01:13:33,840 --> 01:13:36,440
I explained to him the meaning of this house.

926
01:13:37,160 --> 01:13:38,440
I told him I wanted it for my wife.

927
01:13:39,080 --> 01:13:40,560
I explained how much it means to her.

928
01:13:42,560 --> 01:13:44,200
That was enough for him to sell it to me.

929
01:13:47,920 --> 01:13:49,200
Don't you ever cross my path again.

930
01:13:50,480 --> 01:13:51,560
I've always won.

931
01:13:52,520 --> 01:13:53,200
I'll win again…

932
01:13:59,000 --> 01:13:59,680
You'll be sorry.

933
01:14:17,040 --> 01:14:19,280
There's nothing I wouldn't do to make you happy.

934
01:14:20,880 --> 01:14:23,240
There's no obstacle I can't overcome with your love.

935
01:14:28,680 --> 01:14:30,240
I never used to believe in miracles.

936
01:14:32,040 --> 01:14:34,880
Not until I saw what you could do for me.

937
01:14:37,960 --> 01:14:39,600
You make me believe

938
01:14:40,280 --> 01:14:42,920
that the world can still be like in fairy tales.

939
01:14:46,520 --> 01:14:47,760
Thank you so much.

940
01:14:49,080 --> 01:14:49,520
So much…

941
01:15:38,680 --> 01:15:40,040
I still can't believe it.

942
01:15:40,880 --> 01:15:42,480
Is this house really mine now?

943
01:15:43,520 --> 01:15:44,240
Look.

944
01:15:46,200 --> 01:15:47,520
Your name is on the title deed.

945
01:15:53,960 --> 01:15:57,360
This is the most meaningful, most beautiful gift I've ever received.

946
01:15:58,200 --> 01:15:59,360
Thank you so much.

947
01:16:00,400 --> 01:16:01,920
I've lost count.

948
01:16:02,840 --> 01:16:03,280
Of what?

949
01:16:04,240 --> 01:16:05,760
How many times you've said thank you.

950
01:16:07,600 --> 01:16:09,400
If I knew you'd be this happy,

951
01:16:09,640 --> 01:16:11,520
I would have bought you a village house much sooner.

952
01:16:13,320 --> 01:16:14,360
It wouldn't be the same.

953
01:16:15,880 --> 01:16:17,360
For me, this isn't just any village house.

954
01:16:18,760 --> 01:16:20,440
It's where our love first sprouted.

955
01:16:21,440 --> 01:16:22,800
We experienced so many firsts here.

956
01:16:24,040 --> 01:16:24,680
True.

957
01:16:25,960 --> 01:16:27,120
We watched the stars together.

958
01:16:28,120 --> 01:16:29,720
We shared the same blanket.

959
01:16:31,400 --> 01:16:32,880
We picked greens from the garden.

960
01:16:34,760 --> 01:16:35,680
You haven't forgotten.

961
01:16:38,560 --> 01:16:40,480
How could I ever forget the moments I shared with you?

962
01:16:43,680 --> 01:16:46,160
With this house, you've gifted me our memories too.

963
01:16:48,000 --> 01:16:48,800
That's why

964
01:16:49,760 --> 01:16:51,160
it holds a completely different place in my heart.

965
01:16:52,520 --> 01:16:54,120
I thank you once again.

966
01:17:03,040 --> 01:17:06,120
Wouldn't it be nice if we never went back and just lived in the village?

967
01:17:09,560 --> 01:17:10,960
Village life is hard.

968
01:17:11,480 --> 01:17:14,800
Spending a few days here is different from living here permanently.

969
01:17:15,560 --> 01:17:17,600
Look at all the hardships we've been through so far.

970
01:17:18,200 --> 01:17:19,440
What could be the worst that happens?

971
01:17:21,480 --> 01:17:23,000
You only understand that when you experience it.

972
01:17:25,240 --> 01:17:26,240
You're so negative.

973
01:17:26,680 --> 01:17:28,240
Why are you trying to scare me off?

974
01:17:29,520 --> 01:17:31,960
I'm sure I can handle anything.

975
01:17:33,000 --> 01:17:36,360
Since you don't want to stay, maybe you're the one who doubts yourself.

976
01:17:37,680 --> 01:17:39,560
It would be a piece of cake for me.

977
01:17:41,240 --> 01:17:42,360
Then drop the argument.

978
01:17:44,120 --> 01:17:44,720
Fine.

979
01:17:45,120 --> 01:17:48,280
We'll stay here until you say let's go.

980
01:17:50,960 --> 01:17:53,040
I bet you'll be packing your bag by tomorrow morning.

981
01:17:53,520 --> 01:17:54,800
What did you say? I couldn't hear you.

982
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:55,640
Nothing.

983
01:17:56,280 --> 01:17:56,720
Nothing.

984
01:18:02,040 --> 01:18:03,280
The village air is so nice, isn't it?

985
01:18:04,160 --> 01:18:04,640
Yes.

986
01:18:05,120 --> 01:18:06,760
There's sun, but it's still cold.

987
01:18:10,040 --> 01:18:12,200
Come on, then. Let's go.

988
01:18:12,640 --> 01:18:13,520
Uncle Durmuş.

989
01:18:14,840 --> 01:18:15,360
Where to?

990
01:18:16,640 --> 01:18:17,960
A traveler must be on their way.

991
01:18:18,880 --> 01:18:22,320
It's time to leave the house to its new owners, my child.

992
01:18:22,920 --> 01:18:23,960
I'll take you.

993
01:18:24,320 --> 01:18:25,440
Thanks, son.

994
01:18:25,480 --> 01:18:27,000
My nephew is coming to get us.

995
01:18:28,280 --> 01:18:30,440
I didn't think you'd leave so soon.

996
01:18:34,400 --> 01:18:36,120
This house is always yours.

997
01:18:36,640 --> 01:18:38,840
Stay as long as you like.

998
01:18:39,040 --> 01:18:40,520
Come whenever you want.

999
01:18:40,800 --> 01:18:42,080
Thank you, kids.

1000
01:18:42,120 --> 01:18:44,280
But a change will be good for us now.

1001
01:18:51,560 --> 01:18:53,080
We'll see you again, my child.

1002
01:18:53,520 --> 01:18:55,480
We're waiting for you at our new home.

1003
01:18:56,160 --> 01:18:57,720
We'll be waiting too.

1004
01:18:57,760 --> 01:18:59,280
Like I said, this is your home.

1005
01:18:59,840 --> 01:19:01,920
Make sure to call us. Don't leave us without news.

1006
01:19:02,720 --> 01:19:04,080
-Don't worry. -Let me kiss you.

1007
01:19:04,280 --> 01:19:05,440
Thank you, son!

1008
01:19:07,240 --> 01:19:07,760
Thank you, son!

1009
01:19:07,840 --> 01:19:09,040
My beautiful girl.

1010
01:19:09,200 --> 01:19:09,880
Thank you, son!

1011
01:19:09,920 --> 01:19:11,520
My dear, dear girl.

1012
01:19:29,800 --> 01:19:32,320
If your intention was to give me medicine... Well, the monkey's eyes are open now.

1013
01:19:38,200 --> 01:19:40,760
Whatever I did, I did to protect you from yourself.

1014
01:19:42,320 --> 01:19:43,840
Was this the best solution you could find?

1015
01:19:44,680 --> 01:19:46,600
Were you protecting your child by poisoning her?

1016
01:19:47,520 --> 01:19:48,960
I didn't poison anyone.

1017
01:19:49,600 --> 01:19:51,680
I'm just trying to calm you down.

1018
01:19:56,440 --> 01:19:59,880
You'll understand me when you become a mother, what it means to worry about your child.

1019
01:20:02,360 --> 01:20:03,200
I will not!

1020
01:20:04,240 --> 01:20:04,920
Never!

1021
01:20:05,840 --> 01:20:07,400
I will never forgive you!

1022
01:20:10,440 --> 01:20:12,160
Stay at the house in Üsküdar for a while.

1023
01:20:13,160 --> 01:20:14,600
You'll go and settle there tomorrow.

1024
01:20:16,600 --> 01:20:18,240
Oh, how lovely.

1025
01:20:18,840 --> 01:20:20,040
You've got it all planned out.

1026
01:20:21,000 --> 01:20:23,440
I wish you'd asked me if I even wanted to go.

1027
01:20:24,480 --> 01:20:25,960
Get a hold of yourself, Aslı!

1028
01:20:26,880 --> 01:20:28,880
When will you ever learn to be smart?

1029
01:20:32,880 --> 01:20:35,880
It's for everyone's good that you leave the mansion before Ateş returns.

1030
01:20:35,960 --> 01:20:36,880
Yours most of all.

1031
01:20:38,800 --> 01:20:40,200
I'm not going anywhere!

1032
01:20:40,960 --> 01:20:42,400
I'm not about to leave the field wide open!

1033
01:20:43,440 --> 01:20:45,640
I didn't ask you if you would go!

1034
01:20:46,080 --> 01:20:47,200
I told you, you are going!

1035
01:20:47,920 --> 01:20:48,960
And you will go!

1036
01:21:44,600 --> 01:21:46,280
Welcome, Mrs. Ayşe.

1037
01:21:46,680 --> 01:21:47,720
No one's home.

1038
01:21:49,880 --> 01:21:51,400
You must really like the mansion.

1039
01:21:51,440 --> 01:21:53,440
You're always showing up here.

1040
01:21:53,760 --> 01:21:55,920
You don't give us a chance to miss you.

1041
01:21:57,520 --> 01:21:58,000
I...

1042
01:21:58,520 --> 01:22:01,680
I would have liked to chat with you but...

1043
01:22:02,640 --> 01:22:06,640
I unfortunately cannot tolerate common people.

1044
01:22:07,720 --> 01:22:09,880
Don't worry. I won't stay long.

1045
01:22:10,600 --> 01:22:11,880
Do you know why?

1046
01:22:15,920 --> 01:22:18,400
Because I can't tolerate mothers who make up the lie 'your father is sick'

1047
01:22:18,440 --> 01:22:21,320
just so their son will return to Cairo.

1048
01:22:24,880 --> 01:22:28,040
You might fool Çiçek and Mother Binnaz with your lies.

1049
01:22:28,840 --> 01:22:30,000
What nonsense are you talking?

1050
01:22:31,000 --> 01:22:33,080
What lie? There's no lie!

1051
01:22:33,640 --> 01:22:35,880
I told my son exactly what the situation was.

1052
01:22:36,600 --> 01:22:39,480
One moment, my queen, I'll disprove you with your own voice.

1053
01:22:45,920 --> 01:22:47,120
Malik wants Çiçek,

1054
01:22:47,520 --> 01:22:48,520
and he doesn't want anyone else.

1055
01:22:49,920 --> 01:22:51,960
Don't worry, I'll bring him with me.

1056
01:22:52,640 --> 01:22:56,280
Thank God for translation apps. Technology is a wonderful thing.

1057
01:22:56,560 --> 01:22:59,480
I understood every word you said, word for word.

1058
01:23:04,280 --> 01:23:06,400
When Malik hears this, he won't need a translation.

1059
01:23:08,320 --> 01:23:11,720
Let's see what he does when he finds out about his mother's schemes.

1060
01:23:14,840 --> 01:23:18,360
What's wrong? You look pale. Are you okay?

1061
01:23:20,440 --> 01:23:21,160
You...

1062
01:23:22,360 --> 01:23:23,960
If you keep your mouth shut...

1063
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:27,080
I'll give you a lot of money.

1064
01:23:28,160 --> 01:23:29,640
As much as you want.

1065
01:23:30,800 --> 01:23:34,320
At least you'll escape this miserable life.

1066
01:24:04,280 --> 01:24:06,560
The arugula smells lovely. Doesn't it?

1067
01:24:07,080 --> 01:24:07,800
Yes.

1068
01:24:12,880 --> 01:24:13,400
Taste it.

1069
01:24:18,600 --> 01:24:20,320
Delicious. Wonderful.

1070
01:24:23,920 --> 01:24:27,800
There's nothing like picking your own greens and vegetables from your garden.

1071
01:24:28,360 --> 01:24:29,320
Everything is organic.

1072
01:24:30,120 --> 01:24:32,440
You don't worry if pesticides were used.

1073
01:24:33,160 --> 01:24:36,000
It's not just the food, the air is perfectly clean here too.

1074
01:24:36,640 --> 01:24:39,120
No exhaust fumes. Everything is green.

1075
01:24:39,160 --> 01:24:40,640
The birds are singing.

1076
01:24:41,800 --> 01:24:43,640
Village life really is magnificent.

1077
01:24:49,480 --> 01:24:50,400
Why are you smiling like that?

1078
01:24:52,400 --> 01:24:54,480
Oh, nothing. Just remembered something funny.

1079
01:24:56,320 --> 01:24:57,080
Liar.

1080
01:24:58,040 --> 01:25:00,600
I know what's behind that mischievous smile.

1081
01:25:02,600 --> 01:25:03,280
What?

1082
01:25:04,240 --> 01:25:05,800
Have you started reading minds too?

1083
01:25:06,560 --> 01:25:08,160
If it's your mind we're talking about, yes.

1084
01:25:10,000 --> 01:25:12,160
You think I won't be able to handle village life, don't you?

1085
01:25:12,680 --> 01:25:14,120
Don't even try to deny it.

1086
01:25:14,320 --> 01:25:15,520
Why would I deny it?

1087
01:25:16,080 --> 01:25:17,640
It's just... I don't think that.

1088
01:25:18,600 --> 01:25:20,400
I know for a fact you won't last.

1089
01:25:21,680 --> 01:25:24,760
I'll last so long, you'll regret saying that.

1090
01:25:27,080 --> 01:25:27,880
I highly doubt it.

1091
01:25:28,560 --> 01:25:31,120
You'll be the one regretting being so sure of yourself.

1092
01:25:31,800 --> 01:25:34,280
I think you should give up on your claim while you still can.

1093
01:25:34,480 --> 01:25:35,200
Never.

1094
01:25:36,240 --> 01:25:38,280
Do you think I'm some delicate, spoiled girl?

1095
01:25:38,800 --> 01:25:39,560
I don't think that.

1096
01:25:40,960 --> 01:25:42,360
I know it.

1097
01:25:43,160 --> 01:25:43,560
Fine.

1098
01:25:44,480 --> 01:25:46,120
You keep thinking that!

1099
01:25:46,520 --> 01:25:48,240
I'll prove you wrong!

1100
01:25:49,760 --> 01:25:53,040
Looks like I'll be waiting a long time.

1101
01:25:54,560 --> 01:25:55,120
You're so annoying!

1102
01:26:03,840 --> 01:26:05,280
Let me go! Stop hugging me!

1103
01:26:05,320 --> 01:26:06,120
No!

1104
01:26:06,280 --> 01:26:08,200
-I said let go! -And I said no.

1105
01:26:11,920 --> 01:26:12,880
You're so sweet.

1106
01:26:13,720 --> 01:26:17,360
You get even sweeter when you're angry.

1107
01:26:19,000 --> 01:26:22,080
You can't win me over with sweet words and a smile.

1108
01:26:24,280 --> 01:26:25,600
What should I do then?

1109
01:26:31,520 --> 01:26:33,080
Maybe I'll forgive you if you beg.

1110
01:26:40,320 --> 01:26:40,960
Ateş!

1111
01:26:40,960 --> 01:26:42,160
Turn off the tap!

1112
01:26:42,760 --> 01:26:45,320
I would if I could!

1113
01:26:55,520 --> 01:26:57,440
Look at you. You're like a drowned rat.

1114
01:26:57,720 --> 01:26:59,160
Like you're any different.

1115
01:26:59,440 --> 01:27:00,480
Turn it off.

1116
01:27:19,680 --> 01:27:20,880
Keep going...

1117
01:27:21,880 --> 01:27:23,560
Enjoy the moment you're living in.

1118
01:27:24,720 --> 01:27:26,320
Because this happy picture won't last long.

1119
01:27:36,960 --> 01:27:37,760
Did you hear that too?

1120
01:27:43,280 --> 01:27:43,920
Damn it!

1121
01:27:59,560 --> 01:28:01,440
It sounded like a phone ringing.

1122
01:28:01,920 --> 01:28:02,920
No...

1123
01:28:05,200 --> 01:28:07,240
Ateş! Do something! Turn off the tap!

1124
01:28:18,880 --> 01:28:21,200
Okay. Come on.

1125
01:28:24,200 --> 01:28:25,960
Bro, why did you reject the call?

1126
01:28:26,600 --> 01:28:27,920
Do you have important business?

1127
01:28:28,080 --> 01:28:30,800
Well, why didn't you answer and tell me that then?

1128
01:29:45,000 --> 01:29:45,720
Mercan.

1129
01:29:46,840 --> 01:29:48,280
Can you pass me the wrench?

1130
01:29:54,840 --> 01:29:55,400
Hey!

1131
01:29:57,240 --> 01:29:57,800
Mercan.

1132
01:30:02,080 --> 01:30:03,360
Can you pass me the wrench?

1133
01:30:03,640 --> 01:30:04,680
Okay.

1134
01:30:06,600 --> 01:30:07,000
Here.

1135
01:30:07,840 --> 01:30:08,480
Wait a minute.

1136
01:30:12,680 --> 01:30:13,080
What is this?

1137
01:30:14,240 --> 01:30:14,720
What is what?

1138
01:30:15,560 --> 01:30:16,160
What is this?

1139
01:30:16,840 --> 01:30:19,560
I ask for a wrench, and you give me pliers.

1140
01:30:22,400 --> 01:30:23,280
Did I do that?

1141
01:30:26,560 --> 01:30:27,240
Hey!

1142
01:30:28,600 --> 01:30:29,960
I think you should come back to us.

1143
01:30:31,600 --> 01:30:32,680
Where is your mind?

1144
01:30:33,240 --> 01:30:33,920
On you.

1145
01:30:36,520 --> 01:30:38,400
I mean... on the work you're doing.

1146
01:30:41,840 --> 01:30:42,600
On me?

1147
01:30:43,720 --> 01:30:44,560
Or on the work I'm doing?

1148
01:30:44,720 --> 01:30:46,160
I said on the work you're doing.

1149
01:30:48,560 --> 01:30:50,760
But before that, you said "on you". Admit it.

1150
01:30:52,920 --> 01:30:54,160
You were watching me, weren't you?

1151
01:30:55,240 --> 01:30:56,400
What does that have to do with it?

1152
01:30:57,560 --> 01:30:58,560
It has everything to do with it.

1153
01:31:00,600 --> 01:31:01,960
I saw how you were looking at me.

1154
01:31:04,440 --> 01:31:06,640
How was I looking at you?

1155
01:31:08,640 --> 01:31:09,400
With love.

1156
01:31:12,280 --> 01:31:13,200
With admiration.

1157
01:31:17,800 --> 01:31:18,600
With passion.

1158
01:31:30,960 --> 01:31:31,960
The wrench.

1159
01:31:35,120 --> 01:31:36,040
Um...

1160
01:31:37,000 --> 01:31:37,520
I should go and...

1161
01:31:38,480 --> 01:31:41,480
throw some wood on the fire. We can dry off and get warm.

1162
01:31:46,680 --> 01:31:47,800
Can't we just hug?

1163
01:31:49,440 --> 01:31:51,000
No, I'll go add wood.

1164
01:32:04,200 --> 01:32:04,920
You...

1165
01:32:06,120 --> 01:32:07,720
If you keep your mouth shut...

1166
01:32:08,800 --> 01:32:10,920
I'll give you a lot of money.

1167
01:32:11,960 --> 01:32:13,520
As much as you want.

1168
01:32:14,600 --> 01:32:18,120
At least you'll escape this miserable life.

1169
01:32:21,280 --> 01:32:22,320
Look at this woman.

1170
01:32:22,880 --> 01:32:24,880
She's the type to give the devil a run for his money.

1171
01:32:26,360 --> 01:32:27,960
If Çiçek and Mother Binnaz found out,

1172
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:30,680
they'd probably chase the Egyptian queen with sticks.

1173
01:32:37,160 --> 01:32:38,560
Part of me says go and tell them everything.

1174
01:32:39,840 --> 01:32:40,600
After all...

1175
01:32:47,480 --> 01:32:49,920
the Güneş family is my family now.

1176
01:32:51,920 --> 01:32:53,080
It wouldn't be right to betray them.

1177
01:32:57,520 --> 01:32:59,960
Another part of me says, "don't get involved in this, you'll be the one who gets hurt."

1178
01:33:05,720 --> 01:33:06,280
My wife.

1179
01:33:11,040 --> 01:33:11,680
What's wrong?

1180
01:33:13,520 --> 01:33:15,120
-Are you okay, my wife? -I'm fine.

1181
01:33:16,520 --> 01:33:18,240
You seem distant.

1182
01:33:18,840 --> 01:33:19,520
I'm fine.

1183
01:33:20,360 --> 01:33:23,800
Are you still dwelling on what Mrs. Müzeyyen did?

1184
01:33:23,800 --> 01:33:25,400
Why would I dwell on that wretched woman?

1185
01:33:26,000 --> 01:33:27,800
I have a solid husband behind me.

1186
01:33:28,160 --> 01:33:29,400
He protects me from everyone.

1187
01:33:33,840 --> 01:33:36,360
Of course I'll protect you. I'll protect you.

1188
01:33:37,320 --> 01:33:40,800
Anyone who upsets my wife will get a knuckle sandwich.

1189
01:33:42,480 --> 01:33:44,000
Don't you worry, my beautiful wife.

1190
01:33:44,160 --> 01:33:45,280
My lion of a husband.

1191
01:33:46,280 --> 01:33:47,280
My tiger of a husband.

1192
01:33:50,080 --> 01:33:52,880
Then kiss my lion side.

1193
01:33:56,040 --> 01:33:57,160
And also my tiger side.

1194
01:34:01,720 --> 01:34:04,080
My beautiful wife. My one and only.

1195
01:34:04,600 --> 01:34:06,680
Come here, let me hug you.

1196
01:34:36,200 --> 01:34:37,360
-Move over there. -Oh, for heaven's sake!

1197
01:34:38,280 --> 01:34:40,120
The traffic is a mess.

1198
01:35:04,360 --> 01:35:07,720
You seem down. Did something happen? Something's definitely happened.

1199
01:35:08,720 --> 01:35:09,800
No, nothing happened.

1200
01:35:10,440 --> 01:35:11,360
That's the problem.

1201
01:35:12,040 --> 01:35:13,040
I didn't understand a thing.

1202
01:35:15,120 --> 01:35:16,360
Someone's on my mind.

1203
01:35:17,240 --> 01:35:19,960
Hmm. Sounds like an emotional issue.

1204
01:35:21,200 --> 01:35:22,000
Seems like it.

1205
01:35:22,840 --> 01:35:25,560
Well? Tell me what happened.

1206
01:35:29,480 --> 01:35:30,720
They're acting strange.

1207
01:35:31,440 --> 01:35:34,560
Their mannerisms make me think they like me.

1208
01:35:34,920 --> 01:35:36,840
But they don't make the slightest move.

1209
01:35:36,920 --> 01:35:39,160
They don't say anything about their feelings.

1210
01:35:39,640 --> 01:35:41,480
When that happens, I start to doubt myself.

1211
01:35:42,240 --> 01:35:45,920
Maybe they don't like me, maybe it's just my wishful thinking.

1212
01:35:47,320 --> 01:35:48,800
I think you should trust your feelings.

1213
01:35:49,040 --> 01:35:50,680
Don't doubt their interest.

1214
01:35:51,160 --> 01:35:52,280
Do you think so?

1215
01:35:53,560 --> 01:35:57,280
Silence doesn't always mean denial.

1216
01:35:57,560 --> 01:35:59,760
Not everyone can play their cards openly.

1217
01:36:00,480 --> 01:36:02,040
They can't easily put their feelings into words.

1218
01:36:03,080 --> 01:36:04,280
I wish they could.

1219
01:36:05,160 --> 01:36:07,440
Then the knot would be untied.

1220
01:36:07,880 --> 01:36:11,520
It's not easy for a shy person.

1221
01:36:11,680 --> 01:36:13,000
It's not easy for Cemal either.

1222
01:36:13,280 --> 01:36:15,160
Be a little patient.

1223
01:36:39,240 --> 01:36:40,480
It's bone dry now.

1224
01:36:42,480 --> 01:36:43,480
Are you warming up a bit?

1225
01:36:44,760 --> 01:36:45,320
Yes.

1226
01:36:47,280 --> 01:36:49,000
Good thing you won't get wet again.

1227
01:36:50,520 --> 01:36:51,680
Thanks to you.

1228
01:36:52,360 --> 01:36:55,920
You fixed the tap like an expert who's been doing it for years.

1229
01:36:56,480 --> 01:36:58,080
I didn't know you had such skills.

1230
01:37:00,440 --> 01:37:02,200
For you, I'll be a handyman...

1231
01:37:02,840 --> 01:37:03,760
a gardener...

1232
01:37:05,320 --> 01:37:06,120
a cook...

1233
01:37:09,360 --> 01:37:10,240
Thank you.

1234
01:37:11,320 --> 01:37:13,160
But a simple 'thank you' isn't enough.

1235
01:37:20,080 --> 01:37:20,640
Come on.

1236
01:37:26,800 --> 01:37:27,560
That wasn't enough.

1237
01:37:30,480 --> 01:37:31,000
Okay.

1238
01:37:32,080 --> 01:37:33,440
Ask whatever you want from me.

1239
01:37:34,600 --> 01:37:35,320
Is that so.

1240
01:37:40,560 --> 01:37:41,520
Actually...

1241
01:37:42,040 --> 01:37:45,240
I'd like a nice frothy coffee made by you.

1242
01:37:45,520 --> 01:37:46,800
We can drink it together by the stove.

1243
01:37:47,120 --> 01:37:48,320
-What do you say? -Okay.

1244
01:37:48,880 --> 01:37:49,920
I'd be happy to.

1245
01:38:04,440 --> 01:38:05,560
Help!

1246
01:38:07,200 --> 01:38:07,960
Mercan!

1247
01:38:08,640 --> 01:38:11,240
Ateş! Help!

1248
01:38:12,920 --> 01:38:14,080
What happened? What's wrong!

1249
01:38:16,800 --> 01:38:17,520
I'm so scared.

1250
01:38:18,400 --> 01:38:19,240
Scared of what?

1251
01:38:21,000 --> 01:38:23,160
Look, over there.

1252
01:38:24,040 --> 01:38:25,080
What's over there?

1253
01:38:29,480 --> 01:38:30,160
A spider.

1254
01:38:34,840 --> 01:38:36,640
You were really scared of that?

1255
01:38:37,840 --> 01:38:38,800
What are you laughing at?

1256
01:38:39,880 --> 01:38:42,080
At you. What else would I laugh at?

1257
01:38:42,880 --> 01:38:43,520
Stop laughing.

1258
01:38:46,880 --> 01:38:48,880
I can't help it. I can't control myself.

1259
01:38:49,800 --> 01:38:50,800
At least try.

1260
01:38:51,400 --> 01:38:53,280
Otherwise, the consequences won't be good for you.

1261
01:38:54,080 --> 01:38:56,320
You, who can beat up big men...

1262
01:38:57,120 --> 01:38:59,720
are you really scared of this tiny spider?

1263
01:39:00,360 --> 01:39:01,880
Will you stop making fun of me?

1264
01:39:03,920 --> 01:39:05,480
Okay, okay. I promise I won't laugh.

1265
01:39:09,440 --> 01:39:11,560
Ateş! Enough!

1266
01:39:12,760 --> 01:39:14,960
Okay. I won't laugh.

1267
01:39:15,160 --> 01:39:15,960
You're laughing.

1268
01:39:19,760 --> 01:39:22,640
So you scare my wife, huh!

1269
01:39:23,440 --> 01:39:24,800
My revenge will be terrible.

1270
01:39:25,520 --> 01:39:26,760
Ateş! Don't kill it!

1271
01:39:27,400 --> 01:39:28,440
Don't worry.

1272
01:39:32,880 --> 01:39:33,240
Look...

1273
01:39:33,960 --> 01:39:36,480
Be careful it doesn't jump over here.

1274
01:39:37,640 --> 01:39:38,760
You didn't kill it, did you?

1275
01:39:40,640 --> 01:39:41,120
It's gone.

1276
01:39:41,600 --> 01:39:42,680
I didn't kill it.

1277
01:39:49,360 --> 01:39:50,400
My hero.

1278
01:39:53,040 --> 01:39:54,280
You saved me.

1279
01:39:56,120 --> 01:39:56,880
Thank you so much.

1280
01:39:57,720 --> 01:39:58,320
You...

1281
01:39:59,680 --> 01:40:01,640
Maybe you should reconsider the idea of living in the village?

1282
01:40:03,560 --> 01:40:06,480
Do you think I'd give up because of a tiny spider?

1283
01:40:07,320 --> 01:40:09,320
What would it take for you to give up?

1284
01:40:09,800 --> 01:40:10,920
A tarantula or a snake?

1285
01:40:12,760 --> 01:40:13,520
A snake?

1286
01:40:15,640 --> 01:40:17,320
There aren't any snakes around here, are there?

1287
01:40:18,120 --> 01:40:19,000
Of course there are!

1288
01:40:19,960 --> 01:40:22,480
It's the perfect habitat for snakes.

1289
01:40:22,720 --> 01:40:24,400
Lots of trees and bushes everywhere.

1290
01:40:25,080 --> 01:40:26,800
When they're hungry, they even come into the house.

1291
01:40:28,120 --> 01:40:29,360
It's a village house.

1292
01:40:34,520 --> 01:40:35,280
Ateş!

1293
01:40:39,520 --> 01:40:41,040
What's wrong? Scared?

1294
01:40:43,040 --> 01:40:44,680
-Are you scared or what? -I'm not scared!

1295
01:40:47,560 --> 01:40:50,480
Okay, then I'll go, you make the coffees.

1296
01:40:50,880 --> 01:40:52,960
Ateş! Don't go!

1297
01:40:53,960 --> 01:40:55,760
Why? I'm going to add wood to the fire.

1298
01:40:57,280 --> 01:40:57,920
Don't go.

1299
01:41:00,840 --> 01:41:01,320
Why?

1300
01:41:03,800 --> 01:41:04,280
Well...

1301
01:41:05,080 --> 01:41:08,480
I get bored here all by myself.

1302
01:41:11,640 --> 01:41:14,280
You'll be bored just making coffee?

1303
01:41:18,240 --> 01:41:19,480
I think you're scared.

1304
01:41:20,440 --> 01:41:22,080
I'm not scared.

1305
01:41:22,880 --> 01:41:26,320
But still, don't go.

1306
01:41:28,360 --> 01:41:29,560
My brave wife.

1307
01:41:31,040 --> 01:41:32,560
The bravest of the water fairies.

1308
01:41:35,080 --> 01:41:37,720
Okay. I'll make the coffees.

1309
01:41:38,760 --> 01:41:39,440
You do that.

1310
01:41:59,800 --> 01:42:00,880
Stay right here like that.

1311
01:42:01,000 --> 01:42:01,760
Don't go anywhere.

1312
01:42:01,800 --> 01:42:03,280
I'm not going, don't worry.

1313
01:42:14,200 --> 01:42:17,160
This isn't going to work like this.

1314
01:42:18,600 --> 01:42:20,560
I need to tell her and get it over with.

1315
01:42:31,280 --> 01:42:32,520
Hello!

1316
01:42:35,320 --> 01:42:36,880
Helloooo! Who am I talking to?

1317
01:42:38,240 --> 01:42:38,840
What happened?

1318
01:42:39,240 --> 01:42:40,240
I was lost in thought, sorry.

1319
01:42:41,000 --> 01:42:43,520
I said hello, but you didn't hear me.

1320
01:42:45,480 --> 01:42:48,360
Zehra. You handle these.

1321
01:42:49,280 --> 01:42:52,520
I'm going to take a walk, clear my head a bit.

1322
01:43:00,600 --> 01:43:01,840
What's wrong with Mother Binnaz?

1323
01:43:02,960 --> 01:43:04,040
Nothing's wrong.

1324
01:43:08,120 --> 01:43:09,240
Why are you like this?

1325
01:43:10,800 --> 01:43:12,200
Are you upset because Malik is leaving?

1326
01:43:15,080 --> 01:43:15,880
Why would I be upset?

1327
01:43:16,800 --> 01:43:19,160
He's not leaving for good. He'll come back when his father gets better.

1328
01:43:21,360 --> 01:43:22,880
Don't be so sure.

1329
01:43:23,520 --> 01:43:26,160
That Egyptian queen is a very scheming woman.

1330
01:43:26,400 --> 01:43:28,440
She's so determined to separate you...

1331
01:43:28,440 --> 01:43:32,160
You think everyone is like you.

1332
01:43:33,000 --> 01:43:35,360
I trust Mrs. Ayşe.

1333
01:43:35,400 --> 01:43:37,560
Unlike you, she wants Malik and me to be happy.

1334
01:43:39,440 --> 01:43:41,680
Fine then. Do whatever you want.

1335
01:44:06,680 --> 01:44:08,240
Well done. It's really good.

1336
01:44:08,400 --> 01:44:09,360
Enjoy your meal.

1337
01:44:14,240 --> 01:44:17,320
Don't you think it would be a good idea to renovate the house?

1338
01:44:19,240 --> 01:44:20,040
Okay.

1339
01:44:20,880 --> 01:44:22,000
You're the architect.

1340
01:44:22,800 --> 01:44:24,760
Tell me what you have in mind.

1341
01:44:31,520 --> 01:44:34,440
We could do the ceilings with paneling, for example.

1342
01:44:36,760 --> 01:44:37,760
Could be.

1343
01:44:39,600 --> 01:44:41,160
And we could paint the walls white.

1344
01:44:41,440 --> 01:44:44,120
We can break the monotony by adding horizontal wooden beams.

1345
01:44:45,560 --> 01:44:46,520
Good idea.

1346
01:44:48,400 --> 01:44:50,000
And we could put a stove right there.

1347
01:44:50,200 --> 01:44:53,360
We could toast bread and roast chestnuts on it, it would smell lovely.

1348
01:44:54,240 --> 01:44:55,480
I think it would be great.

1349
01:44:56,880 --> 01:45:02,040
Across from the fireplace, we could put a fluffy red couch.

1350
01:45:02,840 --> 01:45:03,720
Red, huh?

1351
01:45:05,560 --> 01:45:07,000
A bold color.

1352
01:45:07,280 --> 01:45:08,480
But I think it would look good too.

1353
01:45:09,960 --> 01:45:10,720
Amazing.

1354
01:45:12,040 --> 01:45:13,760
You didn't object to a single thing I said.

1355
01:45:16,680 --> 01:45:18,440
I'm following Uncle Durmuş's advice.

1356
01:45:19,160 --> 01:45:20,160
Say "yes" to everything.

1357
01:45:21,200 --> 01:45:23,120
Good job. Keep it up.

1358
01:45:29,800 --> 01:45:31,520
The power's out. What are we going to do now?

1359
01:45:32,120 --> 01:45:33,840
The fuse might have tripped.

1360
01:45:34,080 --> 01:45:36,760
Calm down, you wait here. Let me check.

1361
01:45:37,400 --> 01:45:38,680
Okay. Come back quickly.

1362
01:46:10,600 --> 01:46:11,440
Ateş!

1363
01:46:13,320 --> 01:46:14,640
Ateş! Answer me!

1364
01:46:16,120 --> 01:46:17,480
Ateş! Where are you?

1365
01:46:19,760 --> 01:46:20,680
Where is he?

1366
01:46:32,760 --> 01:46:33,800
Ateş!

1367
01:46:42,040 --> 01:46:42,800
Ateş!

1368
01:46:47,560 --> 01:46:48,880
Ateş! Where are you?

1369
01:46:51,880 --> 01:46:53,400
Where is this man?

1370
01:46:56,440 --> 01:46:57,640
The opportunity I was waiting for just fell into my lap.

1371
01:47:13,280 --> 01:47:14,080
Damn it!

1372
01:47:24,720 --> 01:47:26,240
I can't see anything.

1373
01:47:29,440 --> 01:47:30,240
Mercan!

1374
01:47:31,720 --> 01:47:32,800
What are you doing here?

1375
01:47:33,800 --> 01:47:35,040
I told you to wait inside.

1376
01:47:36,360 --> 01:47:38,280
I called out, you didn't hear me.

1377
01:47:38,520 --> 01:47:39,680
I was worried about you.

1378
01:47:41,280 --> 01:47:43,000
As you can see, I'm perfectly fine.

1379
01:47:43,800 --> 01:47:45,120
-Yes. -Am I fine?

1380
01:47:45,880 --> 01:47:46,280
Okay.

1381
01:47:49,120 --> 01:47:50,720
It's very cold outside.

1382
01:47:54,560 --> 01:47:55,920
Come on, let's go inside.

1383
01:47:56,840 --> 01:47:57,760
It's so dark.

1384
01:48:28,760 --> 01:48:29,440
My love.

1385
01:48:30,440 --> 01:48:32,040
Why did you call me?

1386
01:48:32,240 --> 01:48:33,360
Welcome.

1387
01:48:33,880 --> 01:48:34,520
Thank you.

1388
01:48:35,120 --> 01:48:37,600
I prepared a dinner for us.

1389
01:48:38,080 --> 01:48:39,080
Just the two of us.

1390
01:48:40,880 --> 01:48:42,120
How thoughtful of you.

1391
01:48:43,680 --> 01:48:44,880
Thank you.

1392
01:48:45,640 --> 01:48:47,880
I made all your favorite dishes.

1393
01:48:47,920 --> 01:48:51,560
I made your favorite soup. All special for you.

1394
01:49:18,720 --> 01:49:20,640
Thank you so much. You're so thoughtful.

1395
01:49:21,280 --> 01:49:22,480
Everything looks wonderful.

1396
01:49:23,120 --> 01:49:23,880
Don't mention it.

1397
01:49:24,560 --> 01:49:25,960
It was my pleasure.

1398
01:49:27,520 --> 01:49:28,400
Come on, sit down.

1399
01:49:30,520 --> 01:49:31,000
Okay.

1400
01:49:40,520 --> 01:49:43,040
I hope you like the taste.

1401
01:49:43,920 --> 01:49:44,760
I'm sure I will.

1402
01:49:45,440 --> 01:49:46,080
I mean...

1403
01:49:48,360 --> 01:49:49,720
The smell is so good.

1404
01:49:49,760 --> 01:49:52,360
It hints at how delicious it will be.

1405
01:49:52,640 --> 01:49:55,080
Come on, taste it.

1406
01:49:55,400 --> 01:49:56,520
Okay, then...

1407
01:50:14,640 --> 01:50:17,200
When you look at me like that, I feel strange.

1408
01:50:18,280 --> 01:50:19,760
I always look at you like this.

1409
01:50:21,560 --> 01:50:22,840
You're so beautiful.

1410
01:50:23,760 --> 01:50:25,040
I can't take my eyes off you.

1411
01:50:26,680 --> 01:50:27,600
I love you so much.

1412
01:50:29,200 --> 01:50:31,080
I love you so much too, habibi.

1413
01:50:32,440 --> 01:50:33,080
Habibti.

1414
01:50:38,920 --> 01:50:40,160
You are my everything.

1415
01:50:41,000 --> 01:50:42,120
My night and day.

1416
01:50:43,120 --> 01:50:44,520
My today and tomorrow.

1417
01:50:46,200 --> 01:50:47,280
My whole world.

1418
01:50:55,800 --> 01:50:56,600
And you are mine.

1419
01:51:06,040 --> 01:51:08,080
Come on, eat your meal before it gets cold.

1420
01:51:08,680 --> 01:51:09,280
Okay.

1421
01:51:21,600 --> 01:51:23,840
How do you manage to make everything so delicious?

1422
01:51:24,760 --> 01:51:26,920
-Have some of the salad too. -I'll eat everything.

1423
01:51:27,640 --> 01:51:28,600
I'll eat it all.

1424
01:51:29,280 --> 01:51:31,040
I made it all for you. Eat plenty.

1425
01:51:46,000 --> 01:51:46,600
Come here, you.

1426
01:51:50,160 --> 01:51:52,600
Did you check the fuse box? Is there a problem?

1427
01:51:53,680 --> 01:51:54,560
I checked.

1428
01:51:55,720 --> 01:51:57,880
The power cut isn't related to the house, I think.

1429
01:51:58,600 --> 01:52:00,000
It seems like a general fault.

1430
01:52:02,000 --> 01:52:03,480
Hopefully it won't last long.

1431
01:52:05,680 --> 01:52:07,360
Unfortunately, it looks like it will.

1432
01:52:08,840 --> 01:52:10,800
Because there's a storm outside.

1433
01:52:11,120 --> 01:52:12,200
Looks like rain.

1434
01:52:19,400 --> 01:52:20,120
You...

1435
01:52:22,120 --> 01:52:24,000
Were you scared of the shadows on the wall?

1436
01:52:30,440 --> 01:52:32,360
We've never played shadow puppets, have we?

1437
01:52:33,520 --> 01:52:34,240
No.

1438
01:52:35,320 --> 01:52:36,000
Shall we?

1439
01:54:16,440 --> 01:54:17,160
The power's back on.

1440
01:54:17,960 --> 01:54:18,720
Yes.

1441
01:54:40,280 --> 01:54:41,880
I feel so peaceful, here on your chest.

1442
01:54:44,280 --> 01:54:44,960
Me too.

1443
01:54:46,520 --> 01:54:48,080
The woman I love, here beside me.

1444
01:54:49,040 --> 01:54:50,600
We're in our warm bed.

1445
01:54:52,000 --> 01:54:53,360
We're in our warm bed. The sound of rain outside.

1446
01:54:55,640 --> 01:54:57,200
I could stay like this forever.

1447
01:54:58,720 --> 01:54:59,920
I think we could.

1448
01:55:00,560 --> 01:55:02,320
We really made progress today.

1449
01:55:02,960 --> 01:55:05,960
We tended the garden, picked the ripe fruit.

1450
01:55:06,280 --> 01:55:07,680
We fixed the tap.

1451
01:55:08,160 --> 01:55:09,920
I'm proud of us.

1452
01:55:10,760 --> 01:55:13,200
The idea of living in the village seems more possible to me now.

1453
01:55:15,600 --> 01:55:17,120
Maybe you were right.

1454
01:55:17,600 --> 01:55:20,760
If we work together, we can do this.

1455
01:55:26,760 --> 01:55:27,640
Get up!

1456
01:55:27,760 --> 01:55:28,800
What happened? Where?

1457
01:55:33,200 --> 01:55:34,600
Water dripped on your head too, didn't it?

1458
01:55:37,120 --> 01:55:38,080
Get up, come on.

1459
01:55:40,000 --> 01:55:42,080
Oh no! The roof is leaking!

1460
01:55:43,320 --> 01:55:45,280
I just had the roof repaired.

1461
01:55:45,640 --> 01:55:47,040
Guess it wasn't done properly.

1462
01:55:47,880 --> 01:55:49,080
Let me go get a bucket.

1463
01:55:49,120 --> 01:55:51,720
Otherwise the bed will get soaked.

1464
01:56:05,880 --> 01:56:06,840
Put it here.

1465
01:56:14,520 --> 01:56:16,800
Well, we've found a temporary solution for now.

1466
01:56:17,560 --> 01:56:19,280
We definitely need to have the roof checked again.

1467
01:56:24,640 --> 01:56:26,360
Do you see what I see?

1468
01:56:27,760 --> 01:56:29,600
I see it. I wish I didn't.

1469
01:56:34,280 --> 01:56:37,920
When I was getting the bucket, I saw a basin in the bathroom. Let me get that.

1470
01:56:38,320 --> 01:56:39,800
Hopefully, this will be it.

1471
01:56:42,920 --> 01:56:43,520
Here, put that there.

1472
01:56:52,520 --> 01:56:55,200
Just pray the roof doesn't collapse on us.

1473
01:56:57,800 --> 01:56:59,080
This can't go on like this.

1474
01:56:59,960 --> 01:57:02,960
You go to the bathroom, and I'll go down to the kitchen.

1475
01:57:03,360 --> 01:57:05,680
Let's get whatever we have, basins, buckets, pots, pans.

1476
01:57:05,720 --> 01:57:06,320
Okay, let's go.

1477
01:57:41,240 --> 01:57:42,520
My lower back is killing me.

1478
01:57:50,440 --> 01:57:51,920
My neck is stiff too.

1479
01:57:53,520 --> 01:57:54,520
What a night, though, right?

1480
01:57:55,880 --> 01:57:57,200
It was a nightmare.

1481
01:57:58,240 --> 01:57:59,400
Look at this mess.

1482
01:57:59,880 --> 01:58:01,920
There's not a pot left in the kitchen.

1483
01:58:03,280 --> 01:58:04,760
If we're going to live in this house...

1484
01:58:05,720 --> 01:58:08,040
we need to renovate everything.

1485
01:58:09,200 --> 01:58:11,880
First priority, the roof, and then the electrical and water systems.

1486
01:58:17,280 --> 01:58:17,960
Well...

1487
01:58:19,960 --> 01:58:20,440
What?

1488
01:58:23,600 --> 01:58:24,800
Actually, I've been thinking…

1489
01:58:25,960 --> 01:58:26,800
Actually...

1490
01:58:30,120 --> 01:58:32,720
Maybe instead of living here permanently,

1491
01:58:33,840 --> 01:58:35,960
it might be more practical to just visit occasionally.

1492
01:58:39,280 --> 01:58:40,040
Meaning?

1493
01:58:42,400 --> 01:58:43,120
Meaning what?

1494
01:58:43,720 --> 01:58:44,840
Meaning I was right?

1495
01:58:49,280 --> 01:58:51,360
Meaning you were right.

1496
01:58:53,200 --> 01:58:55,160
That's more like it. Give me my due.

1497
01:58:56,200 --> 01:58:57,080
I just did.

1498
01:58:57,720 --> 01:58:59,360
Are you walking on air now?

1499
01:58:59,920 --> 01:59:00,520
Yes.

1500
01:59:01,240 --> 01:59:03,160
But you can't see it from down there.

1501
01:59:04,280 --> 01:59:05,800
Don't get too cocky.

1502
01:59:06,400 --> 01:59:07,640
The price could be high.

1503
01:59:08,680 --> 01:59:10,720
Oh my, I'm quiet.

1504
01:59:12,000 --> 01:59:14,040
Enough chit-chat.

1505
01:59:14,760 --> 01:59:16,680
Come on, let's have a nice breakfast.

1506
01:59:16,800 --> 01:59:18,680
Then we can pack our things and leave.

1507
01:59:19,720 --> 01:59:21,800
You pack the blankets and such.

1508
01:59:22,880 --> 01:59:25,040
Life is a shared effort, Mr. Ateş.

1509
01:59:33,920 --> 01:59:34,680
Come on!

1510
01:59:36,720 --> 01:59:37,720
You're still sitting.

1511
01:59:38,600 --> 01:59:41,720
First pack the blankets, then the pots.

1512
02:00:27,280 --> 02:00:28,160
What's going on, my girl?

1513
02:00:29,480 --> 02:00:30,600
Nothing's going on.

1514
02:00:31,160 --> 02:00:32,600
You told me to go. I'm going.

1515
02:00:35,120 --> 02:00:37,200
Thank you for listening to me, my daughter.

1516
02:00:37,960 --> 02:00:40,240
You made the right decision for yourself.

1517
02:00:40,440 --> 02:00:42,080
Believe me, you won't regret it.

1518
02:00:44,560 --> 02:00:45,040
I hope so.

1519
02:00:47,080 --> 02:00:48,640
Leaving your family,

1520
02:00:49,160 --> 02:00:51,400
your loved ones, is never easy.

1521
02:00:52,040 --> 02:00:53,680
Don't think of it as a separation.

1522
02:00:54,840 --> 02:00:56,760
You're just going away for a while.

1523
02:00:59,240 --> 02:01:00,640
And we'll see each other often.

1524
02:01:01,880 --> 02:01:04,000
What you say won't lessen your guilt.

1525
02:01:07,120 --> 02:01:09,120
I know you see me as a burden,

1526
02:01:09,320 --> 02:01:10,680
that you want to get rid of me.

1527
02:01:11,840 --> 02:01:13,000
You're wrong.

1528
02:01:13,600 --> 02:01:17,200
I love you more than anyone or anything in this world.

1529
02:01:20,040 --> 02:01:21,040
Trust me, my child.

1530
02:01:22,040 --> 02:01:24,240
You'll see, very soon everything will be alright.

1531
02:01:41,240 --> 02:01:42,320
I'm leaving, Cemal.

1532
02:01:43,280 --> 02:01:45,840
Because no one loves me. No one wants me.

1533
02:01:47,800 --> 02:01:48,360
Goodbye.

1534
02:01:51,400 --> 02:01:52,640
Is that all you have to say?

1535
02:01:58,520 --> 02:01:59,880
So you don't love me either.

1536
02:02:00,440 --> 02:02:01,360
You don't want me either.

1537
02:02:06,320 --> 02:02:08,240
I need to go to the office, I have work.

1538
02:02:10,440 --> 02:02:11,320
Let me take care of that.

1539
02:02:17,400 --> 02:02:18,640
One day I will come back.

1540
02:02:19,360 --> 02:02:20,960
I'll be everyone's nightmare.

1541
02:02:21,720 --> 02:02:26,160
I will make you pay for everything you've done to me.

1542
02:03:04,720 --> 02:03:05,840
What are you doing here?

1543
02:03:07,240 --> 02:03:08,320
I came to see you.

1544
02:03:09,440 --> 02:03:10,600
How dare you show your face?

1545
02:03:11,720 --> 02:03:14,720
After I got to know you, I felt a connection with you.

1546
02:03:15,400 --> 02:03:16,360
I cared about you.

1547
02:03:18,320 --> 02:03:20,640
Maybe we could make up for lost years...

1548
02:03:21,240 --> 02:03:23,000
Be father and son, I thought.

1549
02:03:24,360 --> 02:03:25,440
But what did you do?

1550
02:03:26,640 --> 02:03:27,880
You lied.

1551
02:03:28,560 --> 02:03:29,800
You sold out your father.

1552
02:03:32,800 --> 02:03:35,400
Your concern was never about being father and son.

1553
02:03:36,880 --> 02:03:39,320
Ateş told me you'd try to use me.

1554
02:03:39,880 --> 02:03:41,120
And he was right.

1555
02:03:43,000 --> 02:03:45,480
I needed to make you believe I would set a trap for Ateş.

1556
02:03:45,760 --> 02:03:47,600
I used the Georgia shipment.

1557
02:03:51,480 --> 02:03:53,760
Ateş knew about everything.

1558
02:03:55,120 --> 02:03:57,160
I would never trap him.

1559
02:03:58,040 --> 02:04:00,040
A son like you is worse than none at all.

1560
02:04:00,920 --> 02:04:03,560
To me, you are nothing but a disappointment.

1561
02:04:05,080 --> 02:04:06,920
I had hoped at first too.

1562
02:04:07,080 --> 02:04:09,040
For a brief moment, I had hope.

1563
02:04:09,800 --> 02:04:11,600
Maybe I could form a good bond with the father

1564
02:04:11,680 --> 02:04:13,520
I've been yearning for all these years.

1565
02:04:17,680 --> 02:04:20,400
But I soon realized you wouldn't be a father to me.

1566
02:04:21,480 --> 02:04:23,600
Because you didn't see me as your son.

1567
02:04:29,840 --> 02:04:31,920
You are the most selfish,

1568
02:04:32,600 --> 02:04:35,760
most opportunistic man I've ever known.

1569
02:04:36,800 --> 02:04:39,160
You can't love anyone but yourself.

1570
02:04:40,360 --> 02:04:43,040
You carry a stone in your chest instead of a heart.

1571
02:04:44,040 --> 02:04:45,800
Your guide isn't love.

1572
02:04:46,480 --> 02:04:47,960
Resentment guides you.

1573
02:04:48,360 --> 02:04:50,440
Rage, hatred, resentment, revenge.

1574
02:04:54,240 --> 02:04:57,280
You didn't approach me because you cared.

1575
02:04:58,360 --> 02:05:00,000
Your aim was to use me.

1576
02:05:01,200 --> 02:05:02,480
Yes, that was my aim.

1577
02:05:03,440 --> 02:05:05,000
But Ateş is no different from me.

1578
02:05:05,480 --> 02:05:07,840
His guides are also rage, hatred, resentment, and revenge.

1579
02:05:08,880 --> 02:05:10,360
He's using you for that.

1580
02:05:11,560 --> 02:05:12,760
If I were you...

1581
02:05:13,520 --> 02:05:15,720
I wouldn't trust that man one bit.

1582
02:05:59,400 --> 02:06:00,400
-This is for you. -This is for you.

1583
02:06:05,280 --> 02:06:06,600
Did you get me künefe?

1584
02:06:07,080 --> 02:06:09,560
Yes. You said you loved it.

1585
02:06:10,640 --> 02:06:12,120
Thank you. You're so thoughtful.

1586
02:06:13,480 --> 02:06:15,160
And you got me chocolate.

1587
02:06:15,960 --> 02:06:17,480
Strawberry-filled too.

1588
02:06:18,760 --> 02:06:19,760
You said you loved it.

1589
02:06:20,200 --> 02:06:22,480
Thank you. You're so thoughtful too.

1590
02:06:34,640 --> 02:06:37,040
It's nicely browned. Just the way I like it.

1591
02:06:37,320 --> 02:06:38,360
Enjoy.

1592
02:06:39,120 --> 02:06:39,720
Thanks.

1593
02:06:45,040 --> 02:06:46,160
Goodbye.

1594
02:06:46,480 --> 02:06:48,280
Safe travels, son.

1595
02:06:48,280 --> 02:06:50,240
May God heal your father.

1596
02:06:50,280 --> 02:06:51,280
Thank you, Mother Binnaz.

1597
02:06:52,680 --> 02:06:54,600
Brother-in-law. God be with you.

1598
02:07:02,000 --> 02:07:04,720
Go, but don't stay away too long.

1599
02:07:05,360 --> 02:07:07,120
Try to come back soon.

1600
02:07:07,960 --> 02:07:10,920
Of course. Besides, if I don't see you for a while...

1601
02:07:11,800 --> 02:07:14,080
You'd miss me. Don't I know it?

1602
02:07:31,440 --> 02:07:32,440
Goodbye, my love.

1603
02:07:33,920 --> 02:07:35,080
Safe travels, my love.

1604
02:08:09,320 --> 02:08:10,560
Çiçek, please don't be sad.

1605
02:08:12,040 --> 02:08:14,880
But this is just a temporary separation. You know that.

1606
02:08:15,680 --> 02:08:16,800
I'll come back soon.

1607
02:08:18,080 --> 02:08:18,960
I hope so.

1608
02:08:20,000 --> 02:08:22,040
Just make sure you come back healthy.

1609
02:08:22,520 --> 02:08:23,600
I'll miss you so much.

1610
02:09:14,360 --> 02:09:15,280
Where are you going, Malik?

1611
02:09:21,880 --> 02:09:24,840
I did some research, and apparently Egypt isn't nice this season.

1612
02:09:36,400 --> 02:09:39,360
Malik. If we don't leave right now, we'll miss the flight.

1613
02:09:39,800 --> 02:09:42,720
I think once Malik hears this recording, he will miss it.

1614
02:09:46,440 --> 02:09:48,320
But don't worry, you'll make it.

1615
02:09:48,840 --> 02:09:49,720
What recording?

1616
02:09:57,400 --> 02:09:57,920
Hello?

1617
02:09:58,640 --> 02:10:00,320
I'll stay here for a bit longer.

1618
02:10:01,600 --> 02:10:03,800
Malek wants Çiçek.

1619
02:10:07,720 --> 02:10:08,640
And no one else.

1620
02:10:09,520 --> 02:10:10,560
Don't worry, I'll bring him with me.

1621
02:10:38,440 --> 02:10:40,600
I never thought you'd be capable of something like this.

1622
02:10:42,080 --> 02:10:44,760
You've caused me the biggest disappointment of my life.

1623
02:10:45,880 --> 02:10:49,200
How can a person tell such a horrible lie to their own child?

1624
02:10:53,360 --> 02:10:56,680
I had no choice, my son.

1625
02:11:00,400 --> 02:11:02,200
I wanted to protect you.

1626
02:11:03,720 --> 02:11:07,200
Getting married would have been the mistake of your life.

1627
02:11:08,080 --> 02:11:08,680
A mistake?

1628
02:11:16,560 --> 02:11:19,360
I made the best decision of my life.

1629
02:11:29,880 --> 02:11:30,440
Enough!

1630
02:11:31,560 --> 02:11:35,600
Someone tell us what's going on!

1631
02:11:36,320 --> 02:11:40,040
Explain so we can understand too! It's obvious Ayşe has been up to something.

1632
02:11:40,080 --> 02:11:42,040
Whatever she said, tell us so we know.

1633
02:11:48,840 --> 02:11:50,160
My father wasn't sick.

1634
02:12:02,160 --> 02:12:05,000
She lied so I would go to Egypt.

1635
02:12:10,680 --> 02:12:12,080
He wasn't sick?

1636
02:12:14,760 --> 02:12:18,040
When this woman exposed her lie, she offered me money to stay quiet.

1637
02:12:22,480 --> 02:12:23,360
What are you saying?

1638
02:12:24,400 --> 02:12:25,040
Oh!

1639
02:12:32,200 --> 02:12:32,960
You did that too?

1640
02:12:40,920 --> 02:12:41,720
Shall I tell you something?

1641
02:12:44,080 --> 02:12:47,080
If you don't want to miss your flight, go.

1642
02:12:50,400 --> 02:12:50,880
Mother.

1643
02:12:51,960 --> 02:12:52,600
Go!

1644
02:13:06,040 --> 02:13:07,560
Thank you so much.

1645
02:13:20,200 --> 02:13:22,520
If it weren't for you, Malik would have left.

1646
02:13:23,600 --> 02:13:25,840
You gave us the greatest wedding gift.

1647
02:13:32,080 --> 02:13:33,120
I knew it!

1648
02:13:34,160 --> 02:13:35,480
I knew you two would get along.

1649
02:13:40,320 --> 02:13:41,800
Bravo, Bride.

1650
02:13:42,640 --> 02:13:46,160
You've proven yourself to be a truly good person.

1651
02:13:48,960 --> 02:13:49,960
Good for you.

1652
02:13:54,640 --> 02:13:57,040
A traveler must be on their way!

1653
02:13:57,320 --> 02:13:59,360
Everyone inside!

1654
02:14:01,200 --> 02:14:01,800
Malik.

1655
02:14:25,560 --> 02:14:27,480
Safe travels, Mrs. Ayşe.

1656
02:14:52,720 --> 02:14:53,840
You didn't forget anything, did you?

1657
02:14:55,360 --> 02:14:55,960
Wait!

1658
02:14:56,720 --> 02:14:59,160
My charger is still in the socket. I'll be right back.

1659
02:15:00,840 --> 02:15:01,760
Check around carefully.
Okay.

1660
02:15:18,800 --> 02:15:19,720
Are we all set?

1661
02:15:22,400 --> 02:15:23,640
Now I forgot my shawl.

1662
02:15:26,320 --> 02:15:27,880
I think we should hit the road now.

1663
02:15:34,240 --> 02:15:34,880
Got it.

1664
02:16:24,280 --> 02:16:24,920
Um...

1665
02:16:26,320 --> 02:16:28,080
The cherry tomatoes were really delicious.

1666
02:16:28,120 --> 02:16:29,280
The greens too.

1667
02:16:29,760 --> 02:16:31,520
Shall we pick some? We can eat them at the mansion.

1668
02:16:31,600 --> 02:16:33,440
If you dawdle any more, we'll be here until evening.

1669
02:16:34,480 --> 02:16:37,840
It'll take ten minutes. We won't be late, don't worry.

1670
02:16:38,480 --> 02:16:39,600
What's wrong with you?

1671
02:16:40,560 --> 02:16:42,320
It's like you're looking for excuses not to leave.

1672
02:16:44,000 --> 02:16:44,720
I don't know.

1673
02:16:46,040 --> 02:16:47,560
I have a bad feeling.

1674
02:16:48,200 --> 02:16:50,120
I feel like something bad is going to happen.

1675
02:16:50,600 --> 02:16:52,160
My feet are dragging.

1676
02:16:53,360 --> 02:16:55,120
Maybe it's because you're leaving here.

1677
02:16:57,440 --> 02:16:58,360
Could be.

1678
02:16:58,720 --> 02:17:00,760
It's not like we're leaving forever.

1679
02:17:01,240 --> 02:17:02,520
This is our home now.

1680
02:17:03,000 --> 02:17:04,680
We can come whenever we want.

1681
02:17:07,480 --> 02:17:09,000
-You're right. -Let's go.

1682
02:17:27,960 --> 02:17:28,960
Oh no!

1683
02:17:29,800 --> 02:17:30,920
The tyre is flat.

1684
02:17:41,960 --> 02:17:43,240
What are we going to do now?

1685
02:17:44,800 --> 02:17:46,400
We need to take this off and put on the spare.

1686
02:17:46,880 --> 02:17:48,280
Let me get the tool kit from inside.

1687
02:17:48,840 --> 02:17:50,120
-You wait here. -Okay.

1688
02:19:18,600 --> 02:19:19,520
Ateş Karahan!

1689
02:19:22,320 --> 02:19:23,080
Mercan.

1690
02:19:28,640 --> 02:19:29,960
You kidnapped my bride-to-be once.

1691
02:19:30,560 --> 02:19:31,120
Look...

1692
02:19:34,960 --> 02:19:36,120
Now I'm doing the kidnapping.

1693
02:19:38,200 --> 02:19:40,360
No. Mercan!

1694
02:19:53,560 --> 02:19:54,400
Mercan!
